70 MachineType MachineTypeFor(maglev::ValueRepresentation repr) {
71  switch (repr) {
72  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
73  return MachineType::AnyTagged();
74  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
75  return MachineType::Int32();
76  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
77  return MachineType::Uint32();
78  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
79  return MachineType::IntPtr();
80  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
81  return MachineType::Float64();
82  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
83  return MachineType::HoleyFloat64();
84  }
85 }

89 // This reducer tracks the Maglev origin of the Turboshaft blocks that we build
90 // during the translation. This is then used when reordering Phi inputs.
91 template <class Next>
92 class BlockOriginTrackingReducer : public Next {
93  public:
94  TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(BlockOriginTracking)
95  void SetMaglevInputBlock(const maglev::BasicBlock* block) {
96  maglev_input_block_ = block;
97  }
98  const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_input_block() const {
99  return maglev_input_block_;
100  }
101  void Bind(Block* block) {
102  Next::Bind(block);
103  // The 1st block we bind doesn't exist in Maglev and is meant to hold
104  // Constants (which in Maglev are not in any block), and thus
105  // {maglev_input_block_} should still be nullptr. In all other cases,
106  // {maglev_input_block_} should not be nullptr.
107  DCHECK_EQ(maglev_input_block_ == nullptr,
108  block == &__ output_graph().StartBlock());
109  turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()] = maglev_input_block_;
110  }
111 
112  const maglev::BasicBlock* GetMaglevOrigin(const Block* block) {
113  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()]);
114  return turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()];
115  }
116 
117  private:
118  const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_input_block_ = nullptr;
119  GrowingBlockSidetable<const maglev::BasicBlock*> turboshaft_block_origins_{
120  __ phase_zone()};
121 };
122 
123 class GeneratorAnalyzer {
124  // A document explaning how generators are handled by the translation can be
125  // found here:
126  //
127  // https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-iFoVuvpIEjA9dtSsOjmKL5vAzzvf0cKI6f4zaObiV8/edit?usp=sharing
128  //
129  //
130  // Because of generator resumes, Maglev graphs can have edges that bypass loop
131  // headers. This actually happens everytime a loop contains a `yield`.
132  // In Turboshaft, however, the loop header must always dominate every block in
133  // the loop, and thus does not allow such edges that bypass the loop header.
134  // For instance,
135  //
136  // function* foo() {
137  // for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
138  // if (i % 2 == 0) {
139  // yield i;
140  // }
141  // }
142  // }
143  //
144  // The corresponding Maglev graph will look something like (this is a little
145  // bit simplified since details don't matter much for this high level
146  // explanation; the drawing in FindLoopHeaderBypasses below gives a more
147  // precise view of what the Maglev graph looks like):
148  //
149  // + 1 ------+
150  // | Switch |
151  // +---------+
152  // / \
153  // / \ |----------------------|
154  // / \ | |
155  // / v v |
156  // / + 2 --------+ |
157  // / | Loop | |
158  // | +-----------+ |
159  // | | |
160  // | | |
161  // v v |
162  // + 4 ------+ + 3 --------------+ |
163  // | Resume | | Branch(i%2==0) | |
164  // +---------+ +-----------------+ |
165  // | / \ |
166  // | / \ |
167  // | / \ |
168  // | + 5 -------+ | |
169  // | | yield i | | |
170  // | +----------+ | |
171  // | | |
172  // |----------------------------| | |
173  // | | |
174  // v v |
175  // + 6 ----------+ |
176  // | i++ | |
177  // | backedge | |
178  // +-------------+ |
179  // | |
180  // |-------------------|
181  //
182  // In this graph, the edge from block 4 to block 6 bypasses the loop header.
183  //
184  //
185  // Note that it's even possible that the graph contains no forward path from
186  // the loop header to the backedge. This happens for instance when the loop
187  // body always unconditionally yields. In such cases, the backedge is always
188  // reached through the main resume switch. For instance:
189  //
190  // function* foo() {
191  // for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
192  // yield i;
193  // }
194  // }
195  //
196  // Will produce the following graph:
197  //
198  // + 1 ------+
199  // | Switch |
200  // +---------+
201  // / \
202  // / \ |-------------|
203  // / \ | |
204  // / v v |
205  // / + 2 --------+ |
206  // / | Loop | |
207  // | +-----------+ |
208  // | | |
209  // | | |
210  // v v |
211  // + 4 ------+ + 3 -------+ |
212  // | Resume | | yield i | |
213  // +---------+ +----------+ |
214  // | |
215  // | |
216  // |----------------------------------------|
217  //
218  //
219  // GeneratorAnalyzer finds the loop in the Maglev graph, and finds the
220  // generator resume edges that bypass loops headers. The GraphBuilder then
221  // uses this information to re-route such edges to loop headers and insert
222  // secondary switches. For instance, the graph right above will be transformed
223  // to something like this:
224  //
225  // + 1 ------+
226  // | Switch |
227  // +---------+
228  // | |
229  // | |
230  // v v
231  // + 2 --------+
232  // | p1 = phi |
233  // +-----------+
234  // |
235  // | |-----------------------|
236  // | | |
237  // v v |
238  // + 3 -----------------+ |
239  // | Loop | |
240  // | p2 = phi(p1,...) | |
241  // +--------------------+ |
242  // | |
243  // | |
244  // v |
245  // + 4 -----------+ |
246  // | Switch(p2) | |
247  // +--------------+ |
248  // / \ |
249  // / \ |
250  // / \ |
251  // v v |
252  // + 5 --------+ + 6 --------+ |
253  // | Resume | | yield i | |
254  // +-----------+ +-----------+ |
255  // | |
256  // | |
257  // |-------------------------------------|
258 
259  public:
260  explicit GeneratorAnalyzer(Zone* phase_zone,
261  maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller)
262  : labeller_(labeller),
263  block_to_header_(phase_zone),
264  visit_queue_(phase_zone) {
265  USE(labeller_);
266  }
267 
268  void Analyze(maglev::Graph* graph) {
269  for (auto it = graph->rbegin(); it != graph->rend(); ++it) {
270  if ((*it)->is_loop()) {
271  FindLoopBody(it);
272  }
273  }
274 
275  FindLoopHeaderBypasses(graph);
276  }
277 
278  bool JumpBypassesHeader(const maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
279  return block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_.contains(target);
280  }
281 
282  const maglev::BasicBlock* GetInnermostBypassedHeader(
283  const maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
284  DCHECK(JumpBypassesHeader(target));
285  return block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_[target];
286  }
287 
288  bool HeaderIsBypassed(const maglev::BasicBlock* header) {
289  DCHECK(header->is_loop());
290  return bypassed_headers_.contains(header);
291  }
292 
293  const maglev::BasicBlock* GetLoopHeader(const maglev::BasicBlock* node) {
294  if (block_to_header_.contains(node)) {
295  return block_to_header_[node];
296  }
297  return nullptr;
298  }
299 
300  bool has_header_bypasses() const { return !bypassed_headers_.empty(); }
301 
302  private:
303  // We consider that every block in between the loop header and the backedge
304  // belongs to the loop. This is a little bit more conservative than necessary
305  // and might include blocks that in fact cannot reach the backedge, but it
306  // makes dealing with exception blocks easier (because they have no explicit
307  // predecessors in Maglev).
308  void FindLoopBody(maglev::BlockConstReverseIterator it) {
309  const maglev::BasicBlock* header = *it;
310  DCHECK(header->is_loop());
311 
312  --it; // Skipping the header, since we consider its loop header to be the
313  // header of their outer loop (if any).
314 
315  const maglev::BasicBlock* backedge_block = header->backedge_predecessor();
316  if (backedge_block == header) {
317  // This is a 1-block loop. Since headers are part of the outer loop, we
318  // have nothing to mark.
319  return;
320  }
321 
322  block_to_header_[backedge_block] = header;
323 
324  for (; *it != backedge_block; --it) {
325  const maglev::BasicBlock* curr = *it;
326  if (block_to_header_.contains(curr)) {
327  // {curr} is part of an inner loop.
328  continue;
329  }
330  block_to_header_[curr] = header;
331  }
332  }
333 
334  void FindLoopHeaderBypasses(maglev::Graph* graph) {
335  // As mentioned earlier, Maglev graphs for resumable generator functions
336  // always start with a main dispatch switch in the 3rd block:
337  //
338  //
339  // + 1 -----------------+
340  // | InitialValues... |
341  // | Jump |
342  // +--------------------+
343  // |
344  // |
345  // v
346  // + 2 --------------------+
347  // | BranchIfRootConstant |
348  // +-----------------------+
349  // / \
350  // / \
351  // / \
352  // / \
353  // v v
354  // + 3 ----------+ + 4 --------------+
355  // | Load state | | Initial setup |
356  // | Switch | | return |
357  // +-------------+ +-----------------+
358  // / | \
359  // / | \
360  // v v v
361  // Resuming in various places
362  //
363  //
364  //
365  // In order to find loop header bypasses, we are looking for cases where
366  // the destination of the dispatch switch (= the successors of block 3) are
367  // inside a loop.
368 
369  constexpr int kGeneratorSwitchBLockIndex = 2;
370  maglev::BasicBlock* generator_switch_block =
371  graph->blocks()[kGeneratorSwitchBLockIndex];
372  DCHECK(generator_switch_block->control_node()->Is<maglev::Switch>());
373 
374  for (maglev::BasicBlock* target : generator_switch_block->successors()) {
375  const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_header = GetLoopHeader(target);
376 
377  if (innermost_header) {
378  // This case bypasses a loop header.
379  RecordHeadersForBypass(target, innermost_header);
380  }
381  }
382  }
383 
384  void RecordHeadersForBypass(maglev::BasicBlock* initial_target,
385  const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_header) {
386  block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_[initial_target] = innermost_header;
387  bypassed_headers_.insert(innermost_header);
388 
389  for (const maglev::BasicBlock* outer_header =
390  GetLoopHeader(innermost_header);
391  outer_header; outer_header = GetLoopHeader(outer_header)) {
392  bypassed_headers_.insert(outer_header);
393  }
394  }
395 
396  maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller_;
397 
398  // Map from blocks inside loops to the header of said loops.
399  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, const maglev::BasicBlock*>
400  block_to_header_;
401 
402  // Map from jump target to the innermost header they bypass.
403  std::unordered_map<const maglev::BasicBlock*, const maglev::BasicBlock*>
404  block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_;
405  // Set of headers that are bypassed because of generator resumes.
406  std::unordered_set<const maglev::BasicBlock*> bypassed_headers_;
407 
408  // {visit_queue_} is used in FindLoopBody to store nodes that still need to be
409  // visited. It is an instance variable in order to reuse its memory more
410  // efficiently.
411  ZoneVector<const maglev::BasicBlock*> visit_queue_;
412 };

414 #define GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(name, deopt_info) \
415  V<FrameState> name; \
416  { \
417  OptionalV<FrameState> _maybe_frame_state = BuildFrameState(deopt_info); \
418  if (!_maybe_frame_state.has_value()) { \
419  DCHECK(bailout_->has_value()); \
420  return maglev::ProcessResult::kAbort; \
421  } \
422  name = _maybe_frame_state.value(); \
423  }
424 
425 constexpr bool TooManyArgumentsForCall(size_t arguments_count) {
426  constexpr int kCalleeCount = 1;
427  constexpr int kFrameStateCount = 1;
428  return (arguments_count + kCalleeCount + kFrameStateCount) >
429  std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max();
430 }
431 
432 #define BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(count) \
433  { \
434  if (TooManyArgumentsForCall(count)) { \
435  *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments; \
436  return maglev::ProcessResult::kAbort; \
437  } \
438  }
439 
440 #define GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state, arguments, \
441  ...) \
442  BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size()); \
443  SetMap(node, GenerateBuiltinCall(node, builtin, frame_state, arguments, \
444  ##__VA_ARGS__));
445 
446 // Turboshaft's MachineOptimizationReducer will sometimes detect that the
447 // condition for a DeoptimizeIf is always true, and replace it with an
448 // unconditional Deoptimize. When this happens, the assembler doesn't emit
449 // anything until the next reachable block is bound, which can lead to some
450 // Variable or OpIndex being Invalid, which can break some assumptions. To avoid
451 // this, the RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE macro can be used to early-return.
452 #define RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE() \
453  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) { \
454  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue; \
455  }
456 
457 // TODO(dmercadier): LazyDeoptOnThrow is currently not very cleanly dealt with.
458 // In Maglev, it is a property of the ExceptionHandlerInfo, which is use by all
459 // throwing nodes and is created in a single place
460 // (MaglevGraphBuilder::AttachExceptionHandlerInfo). However, during the
461 // translation, we create different kind of calls from different places (Call,
462 // CallBuiltin_XXX, CallRuntime_XXX), and non-call nodes can also
463 // LazyDeoptOnThrow (such as GenericBinop) and we always have to manually
464 // remember to pass ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow, which is easy to forget, which can
465 // then easily lead to bugs. A few ideas come to mind:
466 //
467 // - Make ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow non-optional on all throwing nodes. This is a
468 // bit verbose, but at least we won't forget it.
469 //
470 // - Make ThrowingScope automatically annotate all throwing nodes that are
471 // emitted while the scope is active. The Assembler would be doing most of
472 // the work: it would have a "LazyDeoptOnThrowScope" or something similar,
473 // and any throwing node emitted during this scope would have the
474 // LazyDeoptOnThrow property added as needed. All throwing nodes have a
475 // {lazy_deopt_on_throw} field defined by THROWING_OP_BOILERPLATE (except
476 // calls, but we could add it), so it shouldn't be very hard for the
477 // Assembler to deal with this in a unified way.
478 // The downside of this approach is that the interaction between this and
479 // {current_catch_block} (in particular with nested scopes) might introduce
480 // even more complexity and magic in the assembler.
481 
482 class GraphBuildingNodeProcessor {
483  public:
484  using AssemblerT =
485  TSAssembler<BlockOriginTrackingReducer, TurbolevEarlyLoweringReducer,
486  MachineOptimizationReducer, VariableReducer,
487  RequiredOptimizationReducer, ValueNumberingReducer>;
488 
489  GraphBuildingNodeProcessor(
490  PipelineData* data, Graph& graph, Zone* temp_zone,
491  maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit,
492  std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout)
493  : data_(data),
494  temp_zone_(temp_zone),
495  assembler_(data, graph, graph, temp_zone),
496  maglev_compilation_unit_(maglev_compilation_unit),
497  node_mapping_(temp_zone),
498  block_mapping_(temp_zone),
499  regs_to_vars_(temp_zone),
500  loop_single_edge_predecessors_(temp_zone),
501  maglev_representations_(temp_zone),
502  generator_analyzer_(temp_zone,
503  maglev_compilation_unit_->graph_labeller()),
504  bailout_(bailout) {}
505 
506  void PreProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {
507  for (maglev::BasicBlock* block : *graph) {
508  block_mapping_[block] =
509  block->is_loop() ? __ NewLoopHeader() : __ NewBlock();
510  }
511  // Constants are not in a block in Maglev but are in Turboshaft. We bind a
512  // block now, so that Constants can then be emitted.
513  __ Bind(__ NewBlock());
514 
515  // Initializing undefined constant so that we don't need to recreate it too
516  // often.
517  undefined_value_ = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->undefined_value());
518 
519  if (maglev_compilation_unit_->bytecode()
520  .incoming_new_target_or_generator_register()
521  .is_valid()) {
522  // The Maglev graph might contain a RegisterInput for
523  // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister later in the graph, which in
524  // Turboshaft is represented as a Parameter. We create this Parameter
525  // here, because the Instruction Selector tends to be unhappy when
526  // Parameters are defined late in the graph.
527  int new_target_index = Linkage::GetJSCallNewTargetParamIndex(
528  maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
529  new_target_param_ = __ Parameter(
530  new_target_index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), "%new.target");
531  }
532 
533  if (graph->has_resumable_generator()) {
534  generator_analyzer_.Analyze(graph);
535 
536  dummy_object_input_ = __ SmiZeroConstant();
537  dummy_word32_input_ = __ Word32Constant(0);
538  dummy_float64_input_ = __ Float64Constant(0);
539 
540  header_switch_input_ = __ NewVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
541  loop_default_generator_value_ = __ Word32Constant(kDefaultSwitchVarValue);
542  generator_context_ =
543  __ NewLoopInvariantVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
544  __ SetVariable(generator_context_, __ NoContextConstant());
545  }
546 
547  // Maglev nodes often don't have the NativeContext as input, but instead
548  // rely on the MaglevAssembler to provide it during code generation, unlike
549  // Turboshaft nodes, which need the NativeContext as an explicit input if
550  // they use it. We thus emit a single NativeContext constant here, which we
551  // reuse later to construct Turboshaft nodes.
552  native_context_ =
553  __ HeapConstant(broker_->target_native_context().object());
554  }
555 
556  void PostProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {
557  // It can happen that some Maglev loops don't actually loop (the backedge
558  // isn't actually reachable). We can't know this when emitting the header in
559  // Turboshaft, which means that we still emit the header, but then we never
560  // come around to calling FixLoopPhis on it. So, once we've generated the
561  // whole Turboshaft graph, we go over all loop headers, and if some turn out
562  // to not be headers, we turn them into regular merge blocks (and patch
563  // their PendingLoopPhis).
564  for (Block& block : __ output_graph().blocks()) {
565  if (block.IsLoop() && block.PredecessorCount() == 1) {
566  __ output_graph().TurnLoopIntoMerge(&block);
567  }
568  }
569  }
570 
571  // The Maglev graph for resumable generator functions always has the main
572  // dispatch Switch in the same block.
573  bool IsMaglevMainGeneratorSwitchBlock(
574  const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block) {
575  if (!generator_analyzer_.has_header_bypasses()) return false;
576  constexpr int kMainSwitchBlockId = 2;
577  bool is_main_switch_block = maglev_block->id() == kMainSwitchBlockId;
578  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_main_switch_block,
579  maglev_block->control_node()->Is<maglev::Switch>());
580  return is_main_switch_block;
581  }
582 
583  void PostProcessBasicBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block) {}
584  maglev::BlockProcessResult PreProcessBasicBlock(
585  maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block) {
586  // Note that it's important to call SetMaglevInputBlock before calling Bind,
587  // so that BlockOriginTrackingReducer::Bind records the correct predecessor
588  // for the current block.
589  __ SetMaglevInputBlock(maglev_block);
590 
591  is_visiting_generator_main_switch_ =
592  IsMaglevMainGeneratorSwitchBlock(maglev_block);
593 
594  Block* turboshaft_block = Map(maglev_block);
595 
596  if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
597  // The first block for Constants doesn't end with a Jump, so we add one
598  // now.
599  __ Goto(turboshaft_block);
600  }
601 
602 #ifdef DEBUG
603  loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
604  loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;
605  catch_block_begin_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
606 #endif
607 
608  if (maglev_block->is_loop() &&
609  (loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(maglev_block) ||
610  pre_loop_generator_blocks_.contains(maglev_block))) {
611  EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(maglev_block);
612  }
613 
614  if (maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
615  StartExceptionBlock(maglev_block);
616  return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
617  }
618 
619  // SetMaglevInputBlock should have been called before calling Bind, and the
620  // current `maglev_input_block` should thus already be `maglev_block`.
621  DCHECK_EQ(__ maglev_input_block(), maglev_block);
622  if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_block)) {
623  // The current block is not reachable.
624  return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
625  }
626 
627  if (maglev_block->is_loop()) {
628  // The "permutation" stuff that comes afterwards in this function doesn't
629  // apply to loops, since loops always have 2 predecessors in Turboshaft,
630  // and in both Turboshaft and Maglev, the backedge is always the last
631  // predecessors, so we never need to reorder phi inputs.
632  return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
633  } else if (maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
634  // We need to emit the CatchBlockBegin at the begining of this block. Note
635  // that if this block has multiple predecessors (because multiple throwing
636  // operations are caught by the same catch handler), then edge splitting
637  // will have already created CatchBlockBegin operations in the
638  // predecessors, and calling `__ CatchBlockBegin` now will actually only
639  // emit a Phi of the CatchBlockBegin of the predecessors (which is exactly
640  // what we want). See the comment above CatchBlockBegin in
641  // TurboshaftAssemblerOpInterface.
642  catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
643  }
644 
645  // Because of edge splitting in Maglev (which happens on Bind rather than on
646  // Goto), predecessors in the Maglev graph are not always ordered by their
647  // position in the graph (ie, block 4 could be the second predecessor and
648  // block 5 the first one). However, since we're processing the graph "in
649  // order" (because that's how the maglev GraphProcessor works), predecessors
650  // in the Turboshaft graph will be ordered by their position in the graph.
651  // Additionally, optimizations during the translation (like constant folding
652  // by MachineOptimizationReducer) could change control flow and remove
653  // predecessors (by changing a Branch into a Goto for instance).
654  // We thus compute in {predecessor_permutation_} a map from Maglev
655  // predecessor index to Turboshaft predecessor index, and we'll use this
656  // later when emitting Phis to reorder their inputs.
657  predecessor_permutation_.clear();
658  if (maglev_block->has_phi() &&
659  // We ignore this for exception phis since they have no inputs in Maglev
660  // anyways, and in Turboshaft we rely on {regs_to_vars_} to populate
661  // their inputs (and also, Maglev exception blocks have no
662  // predecessors).
663  !maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
664  ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev_block, turboshaft_block, false,
665  false);
666  }
667  return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
668  }
669 
670  void ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block,
671  Block* turboshaft_block,
672  bool skip_backedge,
673  bool ignore_last_predecessor) {
674  // This function is only called for loops that need a "single block
675  // predecessor" (from EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock). The backedge should
676  // always be skipped in thus cases. Additionally, this means that when
677  // even when {maglev_block} is a loop, {turboshaft_block} shouldn't and
678  // should instead be the new single forward predecessor of the loop.
679  DCHECK_EQ(skip_backedge, maglev_block->is_loop());
680  DCHECK(!turboshaft_block->IsLoop());
681 
682  DCHECK(maglev_block->has_phi());
683  DCHECK(turboshaft_block->IsBound());
684  DCHECK_EQ(__ current_block(), turboshaft_block);
685 
686  // Collecting the Maglev predecessors.
687  base::SmallVector<const maglev::BasicBlock*, 16> maglev_predecessors;
688  maglev_predecessors.resize(maglev_block->predecessor_count());
689  for (int i = 0; i < maglev_block->predecessor_count() - skip_backedge;
690  ++i) {
691  maglev_predecessors[i] = maglev_block->predecessor_at(i);
692  }
693 
694  predecessor_permutation_.clear();
695  predecessor_permutation_.resize(maglev_block->predecessor_count(),
696  Block::kInvalidPredecessorIndex);
697  int index = turboshaft_block->PredecessorCount() - 1;
698  // Iterating predecessors from the end (because it's simpler and more
699  // efficient in Turboshaft).
700  for (const Block* pred : turboshaft_block->PredecessorsIterable()) {
701  if (ignore_last_predecessor &&
702  index == turboshaft_block->PredecessorCount() - 1) {
703  // When generator resumes bypass loop headers, we add an additional
704  // predecessor to the header's predecessor (called {pred_for_generator}
705  // in EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock). This block doesn't have Maglev
706  // origin, we thus have to skip it here. To compensate,
707  // MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs will take an additional input for these
708  // cases.
709  index--;
710  continue;
711  }
712  // Finding out to which Maglev predecessor {pred} corresponds.
713  const maglev::BasicBlock* orig = __ GetMaglevOrigin(pred);
714  auto orig_index = *base::index_of(maglev_predecessors, orig);
715 
716  predecessor_permutation_[orig_index] = index;
717  index--;
718  }
719  DCHECK_EQ(index, -1);
720  }
721 
722  // Exceptions Phis are a bit special in Maglev: they have no predecessors, and
723  // get populated on Throw based on values in the FrameState, which can be raw
724  // Int32/Float64. However, they are always Tagged, which means that retagging
725  // happens when they are populated. This can lead to exception Phis having a
726  // mix of tagged and untagged predecessors (the latter would be automatically
727  // retagged). When this happens, we need to manually retag all of the
728  // predecessors of the exception Phis. To do so:
729  //
730  // - If {block} has a single predecessor, it means that it won't have
731  // exception "phis" per se, but just values that have to retag.
732  //
733  // - If {block} has multiple predecessors, then we need to do the retagging
734  // in the predecessors. It's a bit annoying because we've already bound
735  // and finalized all of the predecessors by now. So, we create new
736  // predecessor blocks in which we insert the taggings, patch the old
737  // predecessors to point to the new ones, and update the predecessors of
738  // {block}.
739  void StartExceptionBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler) {
740  Block* turboshaft_catch_handler = Map(maglev_catch_handler);
741  if (turboshaft_catch_handler->PredecessorCount() == 0) {
742  // Some Assembler optimizations made this catch handler not be actually
743  // reachable.
744  return;
745  }
746  if (turboshaft_catch_handler->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
747  StartSinglePredecessorExceptionBlock(maglev_catch_handler,
748  turboshaft_catch_handler);
749  } else {
750  StartMultiPredecessorExceptionBlock(maglev_catch_handler,
751  turboshaft_catch_handler);
752  }
753  }
754  void StartSinglePredecessorExceptionBlock(
755  maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
756  Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
757  if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler)) return;
758  catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
759  if (!maglev_catch_handler->has_phi()) return;
760  InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev_catch_handler);
761  }
762  // InsertTaggingForPhis makes sure that all of the inputs of the exception
763  // phis of {maglev_catch_handler} are tagged. If some aren't tagged, it
764  // inserts a tagging node in the current block and updates the corresponding
765  // Variable.
766  void InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler) {
767  DCHECK(maglev_catch_handler->has_phi());
768 
769  IterCatchHandlerPhis(maglev_catch_handler, [&](interpreter::Register owner,
770  Variable var) {
771  DCHECK_NE(owner, interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
772  V<Any> ts_idx = __ GetVariable(var);
773  DCHECK(maglev_representations_.contains(ts_idx));
774  switch (maglev_representations_[ts_idx]) {
775  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
776  // Already tagged, nothing to do.
777  break;
778  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
779  __ SetVariable(var, __ ConvertInt32ToNumber(V<Word32>::Cast(ts_idx)));
780  break;
781  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
782  __ SetVariable(var,
783  __ ConvertUint32ToNumber(V<Word32>::Cast(ts_idx)));
784  break;
785  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
786  __ SetVariable(
787  var,
788  Float64ToTagged(
789  V<Float64>::Cast(ts_idx),
790  maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
791  break;
792  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
793  __ SetVariable(
794  var, HoleyFloat64ToTagged(V<Float64>::Cast(ts_idx),
795  maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::
796  ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
797  break;
798  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
799  __ SetVariable(var,
800  __ ConvertIntPtrToNumber(V<WordPtr>::Cast(ts_idx)));
801  }
802  });
803  }
804  void StartMultiPredecessorExceptionBlock(
805  maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
806  Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
807  if (!maglev_catch_handler->has_phi()) {
808  // The very simple case: the catch handler didn't have any Phis, we don't
809  // have to do anything complex.
810  if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler)) return;
811  catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
812  return;
813  }
814 
815  // Inserting the tagging in all of the predecessors.
816  auto predecessors = turboshaft_catch_handler->Predecessors();
817  turboshaft_catch_handler->ResetAllPredecessors();
818  base::SmallVector<V<Object>, 16> catch_block_begins;
819  for (Block* predecessor : predecessors) {
820  // Recording the CatchBlockBegin of this predecessor.
821  V<Object> catch_begin = predecessor->begin();
822  DCHECK(Asm().Get(catch_begin).template Is<CatchBlockBeginOp>());
823  catch_block_begins.push_back(catch_begin);
824 
825  TagExceptionPhiInputsForBlock(predecessor, maglev_catch_handler,
826  turboshaft_catch_handler);
827  }
828 
829  // Finally binding the catch handler.
830  __ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler);
831 
832  // We now need to insert a Phi for the CatchBlockBegins of the
833  // predecessors (usually, we would just call `__ CatchBlockbegin`, which
834  // takes care of creating a Phi node if necessary, but this won't work here,
835  // because this mechanisms expects the CatchBlockBegin to be the 1st
836  // instruction of the predecessors, and it isn't the case since the
837  // predecessors are now the blocks with the tagging).
838  catch_block_begin_ = __ Phi(base::VectorOf(catch_block_begins));
839  }
840  void TagExceptionPhiInputsForBlock(Block* old_block,
841  maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
842  Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
843  DCHECK(maglev_catch_handler->has_phi());
844 
845  // We start by patching in-place the predecessors final Goto of {old_block}
846  // to jump to a new block (in which we'll insert the tagging).
847  Block* new_block = __ NewBlock();
848  const GotoOp& old_goto =
849  old_block->LastOperation(__ output_graph()).Cast<GotoOp>();
850  DCHECK_EQ(old_goto.destination, turboshaft_catch_handler);
851  __ output_graph().Replace<GotoOp>(__ output_graph().Index(old_goto),
852  new_block, /* is_backedge */ false);
853  __ AddPredecessor(old_block, new_block, false);
854 
855  // Now, we bind the new block and insert the taggings
856  __ BindReachable(new_block);
857  InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev_catch_handler);
858 
859  // Finally, we just go from this block to the catch handler.
860  __ Goto(turboshaft_catch_handler);
861  }
862 
863  void EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_loop_header) {
864  DCHECK(maglev_loop_header->is_loop());
865 
866  bool has_special_generator_handling = false;
867  V<Word32> switch_var_first_input;
868  if (pre_loop_generator_blocks_.contains(maglev_loop_header)) {
869  // This loop header used to be bypassed by generator resume edges. It will
870  // now act as a secondary switch for the generator resumes.
871  std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>& generator_preds =
872  pre_loop_generator_blocks_[maglev_loop_header];
873  // {generator_preds} contains all of the edges that were bypassing this
874  // loop header. Rather than adding that many predecessors to the loop
875  // header, will create a single predecessor, {pred_for_generator}, to
876  // which all of the edges of {generator_preds} will go.
877  Block* pred_for_generator = __ NewBlock();
878 
879  for (GeneratorSplitEdge pred : generator_preds) {
880  __ Bind(pred.pre_loop_dst);
881  __ SetVariable(header_switch_input_,
882  __ Word32Constant(pred.switch_value));
883  __ Goto(pred_for_generator);
884  }
885 
886  __ Bind(pred_for_generator);
887  switch_var_first_input = __ GetVariable(header_switch_input_);
888  DCHECK(switch_var_first_input.valid());
889 
890  BuildJump(maglev_loop_header);
891 
892  has_special_generator_handling = true;
893  on_generator_switch_loop_ = true;
894  }
895 
896  DCHECK(loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(maglev_loop_header));
897  Block* loop_pred = loop_single_edge_predecessors_[maglev_loop_header];
898  __ Bind(loop_pred);
899 
900  if (maglev_loop_header->has_phi()) {
901  ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev_loop_header, loop_pred, true,
902  has_special_generator_handling);
903 
904  // Now we need to emit Phis (one per loop phi in {block}, which should
905  // contain the same input except for the backedge).
906  loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
907  loop_phis_first_input_index_ = 0;
908  for (maglev::Phi* phi : *maglev_loop_header->phis()) {
909  constexpr int kSkipBackedge = 1;
910  int input_count = phi->input_count() - kSkipBackedge;
911 
912  if (has_special_generator_handling) {
913  // Adding an input to the Phis to account for the additional
914  // generator-related predecessor.
915  V<Any> additional_input;
916  switch (phi->value_representation()) {
917  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
918  additional_input = dummy_object_input_;
919  break;
920  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
921  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
922  additional_input = dummy_word32_input_;
923  break;
924  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
925  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
926  additional_input = dummy_float64_input_;
927  break;
928  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
929  // Maglev doesn't have IntPtr Phis.
930  UNREACHABLE();
931  }
932  loop_phis_first_input_.push_back(
933  MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(phi, input_count, additional_input));
934  } else {
935  loop_phis_first_input_.push_back(
936  MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(phi, input_count));
937  }
938  }
939  }
940 
941  if (has_special_generator_handling) {
942  // We now emit the Phi that will be used in the loop's main switch.
943  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
944  constexpr int kSkipGeneratorPredecessor = 1;
945 
946  // We insert a default input for all of the non-generator predecessor.
947  int input_count_without_generator =
948  loop_pred->PredecessorCount() - kSkipGeneratorPredecessor;
949  DCHECK(loop_default_generator_value_.valid());
950  inputs.insert(inputs.begin(), input_count_without_generator,
951  loop_default_generator_value_);
952 
953  // And we insert the "true" input for the generator predecessor (which is
954  // {pred_for_generator} above).
955  DCHECK(switch_var_first_input.valid());
956  inputs.push_back(switch_var_first_input);
957 
958  __ SetVariable(
959  header_switch_input_,
960  __ Phi(base::VectorOf(inputs), RegisterRepresentation::Word32()));
961  }
962 
963  // Actually jumping to the loop.
964  __ Goto(Map(maglev_loop_header));
965  }
966 
967  void PostPhiProcessing() {
968  // Loop headers that are bypassed because of generators need to be turned
969  // into secondary generator switches (so as to not be bypassed anymore).
970  // Concretely, we split the loop headers in half by inserting a Switch right
971  // after the loop phis have been emitted. Here is a visual representation of
972  // what's happening:
973  //
974  // Before:
975  //
976  // | ----------------------------
977  // | | |
978  // | | |
979  // v v |
980  // +------------------------+ |
981  // | phi_1(...) | |
982  // | ... | |
983  // | phi_k(...) | |
984  // | <some op 1> | |
985  // | ... | |
986  // | <some op n> | |
987  // | Branch | |
988  // +------------------------+ |
989  // | |
990  // | |
991  // v |
992  //
993  //
994  // After:
995  //
996  //
997  // | -----------------------------------
998  // | | |
999  // | | |
1000  // v v |
1001  // +------------------------+ |
1002  // | phi_1(...) | |
1003  // | ... | |
1004  // | phi_k(...) | |
1005  // | Switch | |
1006  // +------------------------+ |
1007  // / | | \ |
1008  // / | | \ |
1009  // / | | \ |
1010  // v v v v |
1011  // +------------------+ |
1012  // | <some op 1> | |
1013  // | ... | |
1014  // | <some op n> | |
1015  // | Branch | |
1016  // +------------------+ |
1017  // | |
1018  // | |
1019  // v |
1020  //
1021  //
1022  // Since `PostPhiProcessing` is called right after all phis have been
1023  // emitted, now is thus the time to split the loop header.
1024 
1025  if (on_generator_switch_loop_) {
1026  const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_loop_header = __ maglev_input_block();
1027  DCHECK(maglev_loop_header->is_loop());
1028  std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>& generator_preds =
1029  pre_loop_generator_blocks_[maglev_loop_header];
1030 
1031  compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
1032  __ output_graph().graph_zone()
1033  -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
1034  generator_preds.size());
1035 
1036  for (int i = 0; static_cast<unsigned int>(i) < generator_preds.size();
1037  i++) {
1038  GeneratorSplitEdge pred = generator_preds[i];
1039  cases[i] = {pred.switch_value, pred.inside_loop_target,
1040  BranchHint::kNone};
1041  }
1042  Block* default_block = __ NewBlock();
1043  __ Switch(__ GetVariable(header_switch_input_),
1044  base::VectorOf(cases, generator_preds.size()), default_block);
1045 
1046  // We now bind {default_block}. It will contain the rest of the loop
1047  // header. The MaglevGraphProcessor will continue to visit the header's
1048  // body as if nothing happened.
1049  __ Bind(default_block);
1050  }
1051  on_generator_switch_loop_ = false;
1052  }
1053 
1054  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Constant* node,
1055  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1056  SetMap(node, __ HeapConstant(node->object().object()));
1057  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1058  }
1059  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::RootConstant* node,
1060  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1061  SetMap(node, __ HeapConstant(MakeRef(broker_, node->DoReify(local_isolate_))
1062  .AsHeapObject()
1063  .object()));
1064  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1065  }
1066  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32Constant* node,
1067  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1068  SetMap(node, __ Word32Constant(node->value()));
1069  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1070  }
1071  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Uint32Constant* node,
1072  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1073  SetMap(node, __ Word32SignHintUnsigned(__ Word32Constant(node->value())));
1074  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1075  }
1076 
1077  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::IntPtrConstant* node,
1078  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1079  SetMap(node, __ WordPtrConstant(node->value()));
1080  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1081  }
1082 
1083  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64Constant* node,
1084  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1085  SetMap(node, __ Float64Constant(node->value()));
1086  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1087  }
1088  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::SmiConstant* node,
1089  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1090  SetMap(node, __ SmiConstant(node->value()));
1091  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1092  }
1093  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TaggedIndexConstant* node,
1094  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1095  // TODO(dmercadier): should this really be a SmiConstant, or rather a
1096  // Word32Constant?
1097  SetMap(node, __ SmiConstant(i::Tagged<Smi>(node->value().ptr())));
1098  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1099  }
1100  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TrustedConstant* node,
1101  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1102  SetMap(node, __ TrustedHeapConstant(node->object().object()));
1103  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1104  }
1105  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::InitialValue* node,
1106  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1107  // TODO(dmercadier): InitialValues are much simpler in Maglev because they
1108  // are mapped directly to interpreter registers, whereas Turbofan changes
1109  // the indices, making everything more complex. We should try to have the
1110  // same InitialValues in Turboshaft as in Maglev, in order to simplify
1111  // things.
1112 #ifdef DEBUG
1113  // We cannot use strdup or something that simple for {debug_name}, because
1114  // it has to be zone allocated rather than heap-allocated, since it won't be
1115  // freed and this would thus cause a leak.
1116  std::string reg_string_name = node->source().ToString();
1117  base::Vector<char> debug_name_arr =
1118  graph_zone()->NewVector<char>(reg_string_name.length() + /* \n */ 1);
1119  snprintf(debug_name_arr.data(), debug_name_arr.length(), "%s",
1120  reg_string_name.c_str());
1121  char* debug_name = debug_name_arr.data();
1122 #else
1123  char* debug_name = nullptr;
1124 #endif
1125  interpreter::Register source = node->source();
1126  V<Object> value;
1127  if (source.is_function_closure()) {
1128  // The function closure is a Parameter rather than an OsrValue even when
1129  // OSR-compiling.
1130  value = __ Parameter(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex,
1131  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
1132  } else if (maglev_compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
1133  int index;
1134  if (source.is_current_context()) {
1135  index = Linkage::kOsrContextSpillSlotIndex;
1136  } else if (source == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1137  index = Linkage::kOsrAccumulatorRegisterIndex;
1138  } else if (source.is_parameter()) {
1139  index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1140  } else {
1141  // For registers, recreate the index computed by FillWithOsrValues in
1142  // BytecodeGraphBuilder.
1143  index = source.index() + InterpreterFrameConstants::kExtraSlotCount +
1144  maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count();
1145  }
1146  value = __ OsrValue(index);
1147  } else {
1148  int index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1149  if (source.is_current_context()) {
1150  index = Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(
1151  maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
1152  } else {
1153  index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1154  }
1155  value = __ Parameter(index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
1156  }
1157  SetMap(node, value);
1158  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1159  }
1160  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::RegisterInput* node,
1161  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1162  DCHECK(maglev_compilation_unit_->bytecode()
1163  .incoming_new_target_or_generator_register()
1164  .is_valid());
1165  DCHECK_EQ(node->input(), kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1166  DCHECK(new_target_param_.valid());
1167  SetMap(node, new_target_param_);
1168  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1169  }
1170 
1171  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::FunctionEntryStackCheck* node,
1172  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1173  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1174  __ JSFunctionEntryStackCheck(native_context(), frame_state);
1175  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1176  }
1177 
1178  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Phi* node,
1179  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1180  int input_count = node->input_count();
1181  RegisterRepresentation rep =
1182  RegisterRepresentationFor(node->value_representation());
1183  if (node->is_exception_phi()) {
1184  if (node->owner() == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1185  DCHECK(catch_block_begin_.valid());
1186  SetMap(node, catch_block_begin_);
1187  } else {
1188  Variable var = regs_to_vars_[node->owner().index()];
1189  SetMap(node, __ GetVariable(var));
1190  // {var} won't be used anymore once we've created the mapping from
1191  // {node} to its value. We thus reset it, in order to avoid Phis being
1192  // created for {var} at later merge points.
1193  __ SetVariable(var, V<Object>::Invalid());
1194  }
1195  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1196  }
1197  if (__ current_block()->IsLoop()) {
1198  DCHECK(state.block()->is_loop());
1199  OpIndex first_phi_input;
1200  if (state.block()->predecessor_count() > 2 ||
1201  generator_analyzer_.HeaderIsBypassed(state.block())) {
1202  // This loop has multiple forward edges in Maglev, so we should have
1203  // created an intermediate block in Turboshaft, which will be the only
1204  // predecessor of the Turboshaft loop, and from which we'll find the
1205  // first input for this loop phi.
1206  DCHECK_EQ(loop_phis_first_input_.size(),
1207  static_cast<size_t>(state.block()->phis()->LengthForTest()));
1208  DCHECK_GE(loop_phis_first_input_index_, 0);
1209  DCHECK_LT(loop_phis_first_input_index_, loop_phis_first_input_.size());
1210  DCHECK(loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(state.block()));
1211  DCHECK_EQ(loop_single_edge_predecessors_[state.block()],
1212  __ current_block()->LastPredecessor());
1213  first_phi_input = loop_phis_first_input_[loop_phis_first_input_index_];
1214  loop_phis_first_input_index_++;
1215  } else {
1216  DCHECK_EQ(input_count, 2);
1217  DCHECK_EQ(state.block()->predecessor_count(), 2);
1218  DCHECK(loop_phis_first_input_.empty());
1219  first_phi_input = Map(node->input(0));
1220  }
1221  SetMap(node, __ PendingLoopPhi(first_phi_input, rep));
1222  } else {
1223  SetMap(node, MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(node, input_count));
1224  }
1225  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1226  }
1227 
1228  V<Any> MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(
1229  maglev::ValueNode* maglev_node, int maglev_input_count,
1230  OptionalV<Any> additional_input = OptionalV<Any>::Nullopt()) {
1231  DCHECK(!predecessor_permutation_.empty());
1232 
1233  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
1234  // Note that it's important to use `current_block()->PredecessorCount()` as
1235  // the size of {inputs}, because some Maglev predecessors could have been
1236  // dropped by Turboshaft during the translation (and thus, `input_count`
1237  // might be too much).
1238  inputs.resize(__ current_block()->PredecessorCount(), {});
1239  for (int i = 0; i < maglev_input_count; ++i) {
1240  if (predecessor_permutation_[i] != Block::kInvalidPredecessorIndex) {
1241  inputs[predecessor_permutation_[i]] =
1242  MapPhiInput(maglev_node->input(i), predecessor_permutation_[i]);
1243  }
1244  }
1245 
1246  if (additional_input.has_value()) {
1247  // When a loop header was bypassed by a generator resume, we insert an
1248  // additional predecessor to the loop, and thus need an additional input
1249  // for the Phis.
1250  inputs[inputs.size() - 1] = additional_input.value();
1251  }
1252 
1253  return __ Phi(
1254  base::VectorOf(inputs),
1255  RegisterRepresentationFor(maglev_node->value_representation()));
1256  }
1257 
1258  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Call* node,
1259  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1260  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1261  V<Object> function = Map(node->function());
1262  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1263 
1264  Builtin builtin;
1265  switch (node->target_type()) {
1266  case maglev::Call::TargetType::kAny:
1267  switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
1268  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1269  builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
1270  break;
1271  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1272  builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
1273  break;
1274  case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
1275  builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny;
1276  break;
1277  }
1278  break;
1279  case maglev::Call::TargetType::kJSFunction:
1280  switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
1281  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1282  builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
1283  break;
1284  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1285  builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
1286  break;
1287  case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
1288  builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsAny;
1289  break;
1290  }
1291  break;
1292  }
1293 
1294  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1295  arguments.push_back(function);
1296  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1297  for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1298  arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1299  }
1300  arguments.push_back(context);
1301 
1302  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1303  base::VectorOf(arguments), node->num_args());
1304 
1305  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1306  }
1307  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallKnownJSFunction* node,
1308  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1309  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1310  V<Object> callee = Map(node->closure());
1311  int actual_parameter_count = JSParameterCount(node->num_args());
1312 
1313  if (node->shared_function_info().HasBuiltinId()) {
1314  // Note that there is no need for a ThrowingScope here:
1315  // GenerateBuiltinCall takes care of creating one.
1316  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1317  arguments.push_back(callee);
1318  arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1319  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(actual_parameter_count));
1320 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1321  arguments.push_back(
1322  __ Word32Constant(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
1323 #endif
1324  arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1325  for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1326  arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1327  }
1328  // Setting missing arguments to Undefined.
1329  for (int i = actual_parameter_count; i < node->expected_parameter_count();
1330  i++) {
1331  arguments.push_back(undefined_value_);
1332  }
1333  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1334  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(
1335  node, node->shared_function_info().builtin_id(), frame_state,
1336  base::VectorOf(arguments),
1337  std::max<int>(actual_parameter_count,
1338  node->expected_parameter_count()));
1339  } else {
1340  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1341  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1342  arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1343  for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1344  arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1345  }
1346  // Setting missing arguments to Undefined.
1347  for (int i = actual_parameter_count; i < node->expected_parameter_count();
1348  i++) {
1349  arguments.push_back(undefined_value_);
1350  }
1351  arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1352  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(actual_parameter_count));
1353 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1354  arguments.push_back(
1355  __ Word32Constant(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
1356 #endif
1357 
1358  // Load the context from {callee}.
1359  OpIndex context =
1360  __ LoadField(callee, AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext());
1361  arguments.push_back(context);
1362 
1363  const CallDescriptor* descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
1364  graph_zone(), false,
1365  std::max<int>(actual_parameter_count,
1366  node->expected_parameter_count()),
1367  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState | CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots);
1368 
1369  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1370 
1371  BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1372  SetMap(node, __ Call(V<CallTarget>::Cast(callee), frame_state,
1373  base::VectorOf(arguments),
1374  TSCallDescriptor::Create(descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1375  lazy_deopt_on_throw,
1376  graph_zone())));
1377  }
1378 
1379  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1380  }
1381  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallKnownApiFunction* node,
1382  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1383  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1384 
1385  if (node->inline_builtin()) {
1386  DCHECK(v8_flags.maglev_inline_api_calls);
1387  // TODO(dmercadier, 40912714, 42203760): The flag maglev_inline_api_calls
1388  // is currently experimental, and it's not clear at this point if it will
1389  // even become non-experimental, so we currently don't support it in the
1390  // Maglev->Turboshaft translation. Note that a quick-fix would be to treat
1391  // kNoProfilingInlined like kNoProfiling, although this would be slower
1392  // than desired.
1393  UNIMPLEMENTED();
1394  }
1395 
1396  V<Object> target =
1397  __ HeapConstant(node->function_template_info().AsHeapObject().object());
1398 
1399  ApiFunction function(node->function_template_info().callback(broker_));
1400  ExternalReference function_ref = ExternalReference::Create(
1401  &function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
1402 
1403  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1404  arguments.push_back(__ ExternalConstant(function_ref));
1405  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1406  arguments.push_back(target);
1407  arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1408  for (maglev::Input arg : node->args()) {
1409  arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1410  }
1411  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1412 
1413  Builtin builtin;
1414  switch (node->mode()) {
1415  case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kNoProfiling:
1416  builtin = Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling;
1417  break;
1418  case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kNoProfilingInlined:
1419  // Handled earlier when checking `node->inline_builtin()`.
1420  UNREACHABLE();
1421  case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kGeneric:
1422  builtin = Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized;
1423  break;
1424  }
1425 
1426  int stack_arg_count = node->num_args() + /* implicit receiver */ 1;
1427  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1428  base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1429 
1430  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1431  }
1432  V<Any> GenerateBuiltinCall(
1433  maglev::NodeBase* node, Builtin builtin,
1434  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
1435  std::optional<int> stack_arg_count = std::nullopt) {
1436  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1437  DCHECK(!TooManyArgumentsForCall(arguments.size()));
1438 
1439  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate_, builtin);
1440  const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor = callable.descriptor();
1441  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1442  graph_zone(), descriptor,
1443  stack_arg_count.has_value() ? stack_arg_count.value()
1444  : descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(),
1445  frame_state.valid() ? CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState
1446  : CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
1447  V<Code> stub_code = __ HeapConstant(callable.code());
1448 
1449  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1450 
1451  return __ Call(stub_code, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1452  TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1453  lazy_deopt_on_throw, graph_zone()));
1454  }
1455  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallBuiltin* node,
1456  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1457  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1458 
1459  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1460  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCountWithoutContext(); i++) {
1461  arguments.push_back(Map(node->input(i)));
1462  }
1463 
1464  if (node->has_feedback()) {
1465  V<Any> feedback_slot;
1466  switch (node->slot_type()) {
1467  case maglev::CallBuiltin::kTaggedIndex:
1468  feedback_slot = __ TaggedIndexConstant(node->feedback().index());
1469  break;
1470  case maglev::CallBuiltin::kSmi:
1471  feedback_slot = __ WordPtrConstant(node->feedback().index());
1472  break;
1473  }
1474  arguments.push_back(feedback_slot);
1475  arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector));
1476  }
1477 
1478  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(node->builtin());
1479  if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
1480  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context_input()));
1481  }
1482 
1483  int stack_arg_count =
1484  node->InputCountWithoutContext() - node->InputsInRegisterCount();
1485  if (node->has_feedback()) {
1486  // We might need to take the feedback slot and vector into account for
1487  // {stack_arg_count}. There are three possibilities:
1488  // 1. Feedback slot and vector are in register.
1489  // 2. Feedback slot is in register and vector is on stack.
1490  // 3. Feedback slot and vector are on stack.
1491  int slot_index = node->InputCountWithoutContext();
1492  int vector_index = slot_index + 1;
1493  if (vector_index < descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
1494  // stack_arg_count is already correct.
1495  } else if (vector_index == descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
1496  // feedback vector is on the stack
1497  stack_arg_count += 1;
1498  } else {
1499  // feedback slot and vector on the stack
1500  stack_arg_count += 2;
1501  }
1502  }
1503 
1504  BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1505  V<Any> call_idx =
1506  GenerateBuiltinCall(node, node->builtin(), frame_state,
1507  base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1508  SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(node, call_idx);
1509 
1510  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1511  }
1512  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallRuntime* node,
1513  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1514  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1515  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1516 
1517  auto c_entry_stub = __ CEntryStubConstant(isolate_, node->ReturnCount());
1518 
1519  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
1520  graph_zone(), node->function_id(), node->num_args(),
1521  Operator::kNoProperties, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState,
1522  lazy_deopt_on_throw);
1523 
1524  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1525  for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1526  arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1527  }
1528 
1529  arguments.push_back(
1530  __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(node->function_id())));
1531  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1532 
1533  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1534 
1535  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state = OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
1536  if (call_descriptor->NeedsFrameState()) {
1537  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state_value, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1538  frame_state = frame_state_value;
1539  }
1540  DCHECK_IMPLIES(lazy_deopt_on_throw == LazyDeoptOnThrow::kYes,
1541  frame_state.has_value());
1542 
1543  BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1544  V<Any> call_idx =
1545  __ Call(c_entry_stub, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1546  TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1547  lazy_deopt_on_throw, graph_zone()));
1548  SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(node, call_idx);
1549 
1550  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1551  }

1553  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole* node,
1554  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1555  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1556 
1557  IF (UNLIKELY(RootEqual(node->value(), RootIndex::kTheHoleValue))) {
1558  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1559  __ CallRuntime_ThrowAccessedUninitializedVariable(
1560  isolate_, frame_state, native_context(), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node),
1561  __ HeapConstant(node->name().object()));
1562  // TODO(dmercadier): use RuntimeAbort here instead of Unreachable.
1563  // However, before doing so, RuntimeAbort should be changed so that 1)
1564  // it's a block terminator and 2) it doesn't call the runtime when
1565  // v8_flags.trap_on_abort is true.
1566  __ Unreachable();
1567  }
1568  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1569  }

1571  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor* node,
1572  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1573  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1574 
1575  V<HeapObject> constructor = Map(node->constructor());
1576  V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(constructor);
1577  static_assert(Map::kBitFieldOffsetEnd + 1 - Map::kBitFieldOffset == 1);
1578  V<Word32> bitfield =
1579  __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField());
1580  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
1581  Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask))) {
1582  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1583  __ CallRuntime_ThrowNotSuperConstructor(
1584  isolate_, frame_state, native_context(), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node),
1585  constructor, Map(node->function()));
1586  // TODO(dmercadier): use RuntimeAbort here instead of Unreachable.
1587  // However, before doing so, RuntimeAbort should be changed so that 1)
1588  // it's a block terminator and 2) it doesn't call the runtime when
1589  // v8_flags.trap_on_abort is true.
1590  __ Unreachable();
1591  }
1592 
1593  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1594  }

1657  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CreateFunctionContext* node,

1677  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::FastCreateClosure* node,
1678  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1679  NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);
1680 
1681  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1682  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1683  V<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_function_info =
1684  __ HeapConstant(node->shared_function_info().object());
1685  V<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
1686  __ HeapConstant(node->feedback_cell().object());
1687 
1688  SetMap(node,
1689  __ CallBuiltin_FastNewClosure(isolate_, frame_state, context,
1690  shared_function_info, feedback_cell));
1691 
1692  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1693  }
1694  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CreateClosure* node,
1695  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1696  NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);
1697 
1698  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1699  V<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_function_info =
1700  __ HeapConstant(node->shared_function_info().object());
1701  V<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
1702  __ HeapConstant(node->feedback_cell().object());
1703 
1704  V<JSFunction> closure;
1705  if (node->pretenured()) {
1706  closure = __ CallRuntime_NewClosure_Tenured(
1707  isolate_, context, shared_function_info, feedback_cell);
1708  } else {
1709  closure = __ CallRuntime_NewClosure(isolate_, context,
1710  shared_function_info, feedback_cell);
1711  }
1712 
1713  SetMap(node, closure);
1714 
1715  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1716  }

1718  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallWithArrayLike* node,
1719  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {

1722  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1723  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1724  V<Object> function = Map(node->function());
1725  V<Object> receiver = Map(node->receiver());
1726  V<Object> arguments_list = Map(node->arguments_list());
1727 
1728  SetMap(node, __ CallBuiltin_CallWithArrayLike(
1729  isolate_, graph_zone(), frame_state, context, receiver,
1730  function, arguments_list, ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
1731

1733  }

1735  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallWithSpread* node,
1736  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1737  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1738 
1739  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1740  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1741  V<Object> function = Map(node->function());
1742  V<Object> spread = Map(node->spread());
1743 
1744  base::SmallVector<V<Object>, 16> arguments_no_spread;
1745  for (auto arg : node->args_no_spread()) {
1746  arguments_no_spread.push_back(Map(arg));
1747  }
1748 
1749  SetMap(node, __ CallBuiltin_CallWithSpread(
1750  isolate_, graph_zone(), frame_state, context, function,
1751  node->num_args_no_spread(), spread,
1752  base::VectorOf(arguments_no_spread),
1753  ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
1754 
1755  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1756  }
1757 
1758  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallForwardVarargs* node,
1759  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1760  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1761 
1762  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1763  V<JSFunction> function = Map(node->function());
1764  V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1765 
1766  base::SmallVector<V<Object>, 16> arguments;
1767  for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1768  arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1769  }
1770  DCHECK_EQ(node->num_args(), arguments.size());
1771 
1772  Builtin builtin;
1773  switch (node->target_type()) {
1774  case maglev::Call::TargetType::kJSFunction:
1775  builtin = Builtin::kCallFunctionForwardVarargs;
1776  break;
1777  case maglev::Call::TargetType::kAny:
1778  builtin = Builtin::kCallForwardVarargs;
1779  break;
1780  }
1781  V<Object> call = __ CallBuiltin_CallForwardVarargs(
1782  isolate_, graph_zone(), builtin, frame_state, context, function,
1783  node->num_args(), node->start_index(), base::VectorOf(arguments),
1784  ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node));
1785 
1786  SetMap(node, call);
1787  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1788  }
1789 
1790  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Construct* node,
1791  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1792  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1793  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1794 
1795  arguments.push_back(Map(node->function()));
1796  arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1797  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1798 
1799 #ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1800  arguments.push_back(__ WordPtrConstant(node->feedback().index()));
1801  arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector));
1802 #endif
1803 
1804  for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1805  arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1806  }
1807 
1808  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1809 
1810 #ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1811  // Construct_WithFeedback can't be called from Turbofan on Arm64, because of
1812  // the stack alignment requirements: the feedback vector is dropped by
1813  // Construct_WithFeedback while the other arguments are passed through to
1814  // Construct. As a result, when the feedback vector is pushed on the stack,
1815  // it should be padded to 16-bytes, but there is no way to express this in
1816  // Turbofan.
1817  // Anyways, long-term we'll want to feedback-specialize Construct in the
1818  // frontend (ie, probably in Maglev), so we don't really need to adapt
1819  // Turbofan to be able to call Construct_WithFeedback on Arm64.
1820  static constexpr int kFeedbackVector = 1;
1821  int stack_arg_count = node->num_args() + kFeedbackVector;
1822  Builtin builtin = Builtin::kConstruct_WithFeedback;
1823 #else
1824  int stack_arg_count = node->num_args();
1825  Builtin builtin = Builtin::kConstruct;
1826 #endif
1827 
1828  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1829  base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1830 
1831  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1832  }
1833  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConstructWithSpread* node,
1834  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1835  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1836 
1837  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1838  arguments.push_back(Map(node->function()));
1839  arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1840  arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args_no_spread()));
1841  arguments.push_back(Map(node->spread()));
1842 
1843  for (auto arg : node->args_no_spread()) {
1844  arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1845  }
1846 
1847  arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1848 
1849  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, Builtin::kConstructWithSpread,
1850  frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1851  node->num_args_no_spread());
1852  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1853  }
1854  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckConstructResult* node,
1855  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1856  SetMap(node, __ CheckConstructResult(Map(node->construct_result_input()),
1857  Map(node->implicit_receiver_input())));
1858  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1859  }

1863  V<Object> construct_result = Map(node->construct_result_input());
1864  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1865  __ CheckDerivedConstructResult(construct_result, frame_state,
1866  native_context(),
1867  ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node));
1868  SetMap(node, construct_result);
1869  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1870  }

2077  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::MapPrototypeGet* node,
2078  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2079  V<Object> table = Map(node->table_input());
2080  V<Smi> key = Map(node->key_input());
2081 
2082  V<Smi> entry = __ FindOrderedHashMapEntry(table, key);
2083  ScopedVar<Object, AssemblerT> result(this, undefined_value_);
2084 
2085  IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(entry, __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(-1)))) {
2086  result =
2087  __ LoadElement(table, AccessBuilderTS::ForOrderedHashMapEntryValue(),
2088  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(entry)));
2089  }
2090 
2091  SetMap(node, result);
2092 
2093  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2094  }
2095 
2096  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::MapPrototypeGetInt32Key* node,
2097  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2098  V<Object> table = Map(node->table_input());
2099  V<Word32> key = Map(node->key_input());
2100 
2101  V<WordPtr> entry = __ FindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key(table, key);
2102  ScopedVar<Object, AssemblerT> result(this, undefined_value_);
2103 
2104  IF_NOT (__ Word32Equal(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(entry), -1)) {
2105  result = __ LoadElement(
2106  table, AccessBuilderTS::ForOrderedHashMapEntryValue(), entry);
2107  }
2108 
2109  SetMap(node, result);
2110 
2111  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2112  }
2113 
2114  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::SetPrototypeHas* node,
2115  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2116  V<Object> table = Map(node->table_input());
2117  V<Smi> key = Map(node->key_input());
2118 
2119  V<Smi> entry = __ FindOrderedHashSetEntry(table, key);
2120  ScopedVar<Object, AssemblerT> result(
2121  this, __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value()));
2122 
2123  IF (__ TaggedEqual(entry, __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(-1)))) {
2124  result = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value());
2125  }
2126  SetMap(node, result);
2127 
2128  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2129  }

2234  frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments));
2235  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

2238  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ForInPrepare* node,
2239  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2240  OpIndex arguments[] = {Map(node->enumerator()),
2241  __ TaggedIndexConstant(node->feedback().index()),
2242  __ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector),
2243  Map(node->context())};
2244 
2245  V<Any> call =
2246  GenerateBuiltinCall(node, Builtin::kForInPrepare,
2247  OptionalV<turboshaft::FrameState>::Nullopt(),
2248  base::VectorOf(arguments));
2249  SetMap(node, __ Projection(call, 0, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()));
2250  second_return_value_ = V<Object>::Cast(
2251  __ Projection(call, 1, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()));
2252  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2253  }

2320  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckNumber* node,
2321  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {

2323  V<Object> input = Map(node->receiver_input());
2324  V<Word32> check;
2325  if (node->mode() == Object::Conversion::kToNumeric) {
2326  check = __ ObjectIsNumberOrBigInt(input);
2327  } else {
2328  DCHECK_EQ(node->mode(), Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
2329  check = __ ObjectIsNumber(input);
2330  }
2331  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber,

2343  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedNumberToInt32* node,
2344  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2345  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2346  V<Object> input = Map(node->input());
2347  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> value(this);
2348  IF (__ IsSmi(input)) {
2349  value = __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(input));
2350  } ELSE {
2351  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ IsHeapNumberMap(__ LoadMapField(input)),
2352  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32,
2353  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2354  value = __ ChangeFloat64ToInt32OrDeopt(
2355  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input)), frame_state,
2356  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
2357  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2358  }
2359  SetMap(node, value);
2360  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2361  }
2362  void CheckMaps(V<Object> receiver_input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
2363  OptionalV<Map> object_map, const FeedbackSource& feedback,
2364  const compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps, bool check_heap_object,
2365  CheckMapsFlags flags) {
2366  Label<> done(this);
2367  if (check_heap_object) {
2368  OpIndex is_smi = __ IsSmi(receiver_input);
2369  if (AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps)) {
2370  // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2371  GOTO_IF(is_smi, done);
2372  } else {
2373  __ DeoptimizeIf(is_smi, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
2374  feedback);
2375  }
2376  }
2377 
2378 #ifdef DEBUG
2379  if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
2380  bool has_migration_targets = false;
2381  for (MapRef map : maps) {
2382  if (map.object()->is_migration_target()) {
2383  has_migration_targets = true;
2384  break;
2385  }
2386  }
2387  DCHECK(has_migration_targets);
2388  }
2389 #endif // DEBUG
2390 
2391  __ CheckMaps(V<HeapObject>::Cast(receiver_input), frame_state, object_map,
2392  maps, flags, feedback);
2393 
2394  if (done.has_incoming_jump()) {
2395  GOTO(done);
2396  BIND(done);
2397  }
2398  }
2399  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckMaps* node,
2400  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2401  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2402  CheckMaps(Map(node->receiver_input()), frame_state, {},
2403  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update(),
2404  node->maps().Clone(graph_zone()),
2405  node->check_type() == maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
2406  CheckMapsFlag::kNone);
2407  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2408  }

2587  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckInt32Condition* node,
2588  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2589  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2590  bool negate_result = false;
2591  V<Word32> cmp = ConvertInt32Compare(node->left_input(), node->right_input(),
2592  node->condition(), &negate_result);
2593  if (negate_result) {
2594  __ DeoptimizeIf(cmp, frame_state, node->deoptimize_reason(),
2595  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2596  } else {
2597  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(cmp, frame_state, node->deoptimize_reason(),
2598  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2599  }
2600  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2601  }

2603  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AllocationBlock* node,
2604  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2605  DCHECK(
2606  node->is_used()); // Should have been dead-code eliminated otherwise.
2607  int size = 0;
2608  for (auto alloc : node->allocation_list()) {
2609  if (!alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() || alloc->HasEscaped()) {
2610  alloc->set_offset(size);
2611  size += alloc->size();
2612  }
2613  }
2614  node->set_size(size);
2615  SetMap(node, __ FinishInitialization(__ Allocate<HeapObject>(
2616  size, node->allocation_type(), kTaggedAligned)));
2617  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2618  }
2619  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::InlinedAllocation* node,
2620  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2621  DCHECK(node->HasBeenAnalysed() &&
2622  node->HasEscaped()); // Would have been removed otherwise.
2623  V<HeapObject> alloc = Map(node->allocation_block());
2624  SetMap(node, __ BitcastWordPtrToHeapObject(__ WordPtrAdd(
2625  __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(alloc), node->offset())));
2626  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2627  }

2632  Map(node->elements_input())));

2634  }

2691  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::HasInPrototypeChain* node,
2692  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2693  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
2694 
2695  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
2696  SetMap(node, __ HasInPrototypeChain(Map(node->object()), node->prototype(),
2697  frame_state, native_context(),
2698  ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
2699  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2700  }

2710  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AllocateElementsArray* node,
2711  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2712  V<Word32> length = Map(node->length_input());
2713  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2714  // Note that {length} cannot be negative (Maglev inserts a check before
2715  // AllocateElementsArray to ensure this).

2717  __ Uint32LessThan(length, JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray),
2718  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kGreaterThanMaxFastElementArray,
2719  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2720  RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
2721 
2722  SetMap(node,

2724  NewArrayOp::Kind::kObject, node->allocation_type()));
