2728  template <typename Node>
2729  maglev::ProcessResult StringConcatHelper(Node* node, V<String> left,
2730  V<String> right) {
2731  // When coming from Turbofan, StringConcat is always guarded by a check that
2732  // the length is less than String::kMaxLength, which prevents StringConcat
2733  // from ever throwing (and as a consequence of this, it does not need a
2734  // Context input). This is not the case for Maglev. To mimic Turbofan's
2735  // behavior, we thus insert here a length check.
2736  // TODO(dmercadier): I'm not convinced that these checks make a lot of
2737  // sense, since they make the graph bigger, and throwing before the builtin
2738  // call to StringConcat isn't super important since throwing is not supposed
2739  // to be fast. We should consider just calling the builtin and letting it
2740  // throw. With LazyDeopOnThrow, this is currently a bit verbose to
2741  // implement, so we should first find a way to have this LazyDeoptOnThrow
2742  // without adding a member to all throwing operations (like adding
2743  // LazyDeoptOnThrow in FrameStateOp).
2744  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
2745 
2746  V<Word32> left_len = __ StringLength(left);
2747  V<Word32> right_len = __ StringLength(right);
2748 
2749  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> len_and_ovf =
2750  __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(left_len, right_len);
2751  V<Word32> len = __ Projection<0>(len_and_ovf);
2752  V<Word32> ovf = __ Projection<1>(len_and_ovf);
2753 
2754  Label<> throw_invalid_length(this);
2755  Label<> done(this);
2756 
2757  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(ovf), throw_invalid_length);
2758  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(len, String::kMaxLength)), done);
2759 
2760  GOTO(throw_invalid_length);
2761  BIND(throw_invalid_length);
2762  {
2763  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
2764  __ CallRuntime_ThrowInvalidStringLength(isolate_, frame_state,
2765  native_context(),
2766  ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node));
2767  // We should not return from Throw.
2768  __ Unreachable();
2769  }
2770 
2771  BIND(done);
2772  SetMap(node, __ StringConcat(__ TagSmi(len), left, right));
2773  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2774  }
2775  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::StringConcat* node,
2776  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2777  V<String> left = Map(node->lhs());
2778  V<String> right = Map(node->rhs());
2779  return StringConcatHelper(node, left, right);
2780  }
2781  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::UnwrapStringWrapper* node,
2782  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2783  V<HeapObject> string_or_wrapper = Map(node->value_input());
2784 
2785  ScopedVar<String, AssemblerT> string(this);
2786  IF (__ ObjectIsString(string_or_wrapper)) {
2787  string = V<String>::Cast(string_or_wrapper);
2788  } ELSE {
2789  string = V<String>::Cast(
2790  __ LoadTaggedField(V<JSPrimitiveWrapper>::Cast(string_or_wrapper),
2791  JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset));
2792  }
2793  SetMap(node, string);
2794  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2795  }

2885  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ToString* node,
2886  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2887  ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
2888 
2889  Label<String> done(this);
2890 
2891  V<Object> value = Map(node->value_input());
2892  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
2893 
2894  GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsString(value), done, V<String>::Cast(value));
2895 
2896  IF_NOT (__ IsSmi(value)) {
2897  if (node->mode() == maglev::ToString::ConversionMode::kConvertSymbol) {
2898  V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2899  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
2900  IF (__ Word32Equal(instance_type, SYMBOL_TYPE)) {
2901  GOTO(done, __ CallRuntime_SymbolDescriptiveString(
2902  isolate_, frame_state, Map(node->context()),
2903  V<Symbol>::Cast(value), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
2904  }
2905  }
2906  }
2907 
2908  GOTO(done,
2909  __ CallBuiltin_ToString(isolate_, frame_state, Map(node->context()),
2910  value, ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
2911 
2912  BIND(done, result);
2913  SetMap(node, result);
2914  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2915  }

2918  NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);

2920  SetMap(node,

2922  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2923  }

2947  template <typename T>
2948  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AbstractLoadTaggedField<T>* node,
2949  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2950  V<Object> value =
2951  __ LoadTaggedField(Map(node->object_input()), node->offset());
2952  SetMap(node, value);
2953 
2954  if (generator_analyzer_.has_header_bypasses() &&
2955  maglev_generator_context_node_ == nullptr &&
2956  node->object_input().node()->template Is<maglev::RegisterInput>() &&
2957  node->offset() == JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset) {
2958  // This is loading the context of a generator for the 1st time. We save it
2959  // in {generator_context_} for later use.
2960  __ SetVariable(generator_context_, value);
2961  maglev_generator_context_node_ = node;
2962  }
2963 
2964  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2965  }
2966  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot* node,
2967  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2968  V<Context> script_context = V<Context>::Cast(Map(node->context()));
2969  V<Object> value = __ LoadTaggedField(script_context, node->offset());
2970  ScopedVar<Object, AssemblerT> result(this, value);
2971  IF_NOT (__ IsSmi(value)) {
2972  V<i::Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2973  IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2974  value_map,
2975  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->context_cell_map())))) {
2976  V<ContextCell> slot = V<ContextCell>::Cast(value);
2977  V<Word32> slot_state =
2978  __ LoadField<Word32>(slot, AccessBuilder::ForContextCellState());
2979  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kConst == 0);
2980  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kSmi == 1);
2981  IF (__ Int32LessThanOrEqual(slot_state,
2982  __ Word32Constant(ContextCell::kSmi))) {
2983  result = __ LoadField<Object>(
2984  slot, AccessBuilder::ForContextCellTaggedValue());
2985  } ELSE {
2986  IF (__ Word32Equal(slot_state,
2987  __ Word32Constant(ContextCell::kInt32))) {
2988  result = V<Number>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
2989  __ LoadField<Word32>(slot,
2990  AccessBuilder::ForContextCellInt32Value()),
2991  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber,
2992  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
2993  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
2994  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero));
2995  } ELSE {
2996  result = __ AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(
2997  __ LoadField<Float64>(
2998  slot, AccessBuilder::ForContextCellFloat64Value()),
2999  isolate_->factory());
3000  }
3001  }
3002  }
3003  }
3004  SetMap(node, result);
3005  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3006  }

3077  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::StoreContextSlotWithWriteBarrier* node,
3078  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3079  V<Context> context = V<i::Context>::Cast(Map(node->context_input()));
3080  V<Object> new_value = Map(node->new_value_input());
3081  V<Object> old_value = __ LoadTaggedField(context, node->offset());
3082  IF (__ IsSmi(old_value)) {
3083  __ Store(context, new_value, StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3084  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
3085  WriteBarrierKind::kFullWriteBarrier, node->offset(), false);
3086  } ELSE {
3087  V<i::Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(old_value);
3088  IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
3089  value_map,
3090  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->context_cell_map())))) {
3091  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
3092  __ CallBuiltin_DetachContextCell(isolate_, frame_state, context,
3093  new_value,
3094  __ WordPtrConstant(node->index()));
3095  } ELSE {
3096  __ Store(context, new_value, StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3097  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
3098  WriteBarrierKind::kFullWriteBarrier, node->offset(), false);
3099  }
3100  }
3101  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3102  }

3170  // For-in specific operations.
3171  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadEnumCacheLength* node,
3172  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3173  V<Word32> bitfield3 =
3174  __ LoadField<Word32>(V<i::Map>::Cast(Map(node->map_input())),
3175  AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3());
3176  V<Word32> length = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
3177  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kMask),
3178  Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kShift);
3179  SetMap(node, length);
3180  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

3182  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared* node,
3183  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3184  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3185  // If the cache length is zero, we don't have any indices, so we know this
3186  // is ok even though the indices are the empty array.
3187  IF_NOT (__ Word32Equal(Map(node->length_input()), 0)) {
3188  // Otherwise, an empty array with non-zero required length is not valid.
3189  V<Word32> condition =
3190  RootEqual(node->indices_input(), RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
3191  __ DeoptimizeIf(condition, frame_state,
3192  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices,
3193  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3194  }
3195  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3196  }
3197  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex* node,
3198  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3199  SetMap(node,
3200  __ LoadFieldByIndex(Map(node->object_input()),
3201  __ UntagSmi(Map<Smi>(node->index_input()))));

3203  }

3205  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadTypedArrayLength* node,
3206  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3207  V<WordPtr> length =
3208  __ LoadField<WordPtr>(Map<JSTypedArray>(node->receiver_input()),
3209  AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayByteLength());
3210 
3211  int shift_size = ElementsKindToShiftSize(node->elements_kind());
3212  if (shift_size > 0) {
3213  DCHECK(shift_size == 1 || shift_size == 2 || shift_size == 3);
3214  length = __ WordPtrShiftRightLogical(length, shift_size);
3215  }
3216  SetMap(node, length);
3217  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3218  }

3222  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3223  __ UintPtrLessThan(__ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(Map(node->index_input())),
3224  Map(node->length_input())),
3225  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,

3331 
3332  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckJSDataViewBounds* node,
3333  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3334  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3335  // Normal DataView (backed by AB / SAB) or non-length tracking backed by
3336  // GSAB.
3337  V<WordPtr> byte_length =
3338  __ LoadField<WordPtr>(Map<JSTypedArray>(node->receiver_input()),
3339  AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewByteLength());
3340 
3341  int element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(node->element_type());
3342  if (element_size > 1) {
3343  // For element_size larger than 1, we need to make sure that {index} is
3344  // less than {byte_length}, but also that {index+element_size} is less
3345  // than {byte_length}. We do this by subtracting {element_size-1} from
3346  // {byte_length}: if the resulting length is greater than 0, then we can
3347  // just treat {element_size} as 1 and check if {index} is less than this
3348  // new {byte_length}.
3349  DCHECK(element_size == 2 || element_size == 4 || element_size == 8);
3350  byte_length = __ WordPtrSub(byte_length, element_size - 1);
3351  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ IntPtrLessThan(byte_length, 0), frame_state,
3352  DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
3353  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3354  }
3355  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3356  __ Uint32LessThan(Map<Word32>(node->index_input()),
3357  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(byte_length)),
3358  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
3359  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3360  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3361  }
3362 
3363  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadSignedIntDataViewElement* node,
3364  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3365  V<JSDataView> data_view = Map<JSDataView>(node->object_input());
3366  V<WordPtr> storage = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
3367  data_view, AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewDataPointer());
3368  V<Word32> is_little_endian =
3369  ToBit(node->is_little_endian_input(),
3370  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kObject);
3371  SetMap(node, __ LoadDataViewElement(
3372  data_view, storage,
3373  __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(Map<Word32>(node->index_input())),
3374  is_little_endian, node->type()));
3375  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3376  }

3433 
3434  void BuildJump(maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
3435  Block* destination = Map(target);
3436  if (target->is_loop() && (target->predecessor_count() > 2 ||
3437  generator_analyzer_.HeaderIsBypassed(target))) {
3438  // This loop has multiple forward edges in Maglev, so we'll create an
3439  // extra block in Turboshaft that will be the only predecessor.
3440  auto it = loop_single_edge_predecessors_.find(target);
3441  if (it != loop_single_edge_predecessors_.end()) {
3442  destination = it->second;
3443  } else {
3444  Block* loop_only_pred = __ NewBlock();
3445  loop_single_edge_predecessors_[target] = loop_only_pred;
3446  destination = loop_only_pred;
3447  }
3448  }
3449  __ Goto(destination);
3450  }
3451 
3452  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Jump* node,
3453  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3454  BuildJump(node->target());
3455  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3456  }
3457  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckpointedJump* node,
3458  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3459  BuildJump(node->target());
3460  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3461  }
3462 
3463  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::JumpLoop* node,
3464  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3465  if (header_switch_input_.valid()) {
3466  __ SetVariable(header_switch_input_, loop_default_generator_value_);
3467  }
3468  __ Goto(Map(node->target()));
3469  FixLoopPhis(node->target());
3470  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3471  }

3502  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TestUndetectable* node,
3503  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3504  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions assumption;
3505  switch (node->check_type()) {
3506  case maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject:
3507  assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone;
3508  break;
3509  case maglev::CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck:
3510  assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject;
3511  break;
3512  }
3513  SetMap(node, ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3514  __ ObjectIs(Map(node->value()),
3515  ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable, assumption)));
3516  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3517  }
3518  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TestTypeOf* node,
3519  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3520  V<Object> input = Map(node->value());
3521  V<Boolean> result;
3522  switch (node->literal()) {
3523  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kNumber:
3524  result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3525  __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumber,
3526  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3527  break;
3528  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kString:
3529  result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3530  __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString,
3531  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3532  break;
3533  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kSymbol:
3534  result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3535  __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol,
3536  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3537  break;
3538  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBigInt:
3539  result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3540  __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt,
3541  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3542  break;
3543  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kFunction:
3544  result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3545  __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable,
3546  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3547  break;
3548  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBoolean:
3549  result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kTrueValue, isolate_),
3550  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value()),
3551  ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ RootEqual(
3552  input, RootIndex::kFalseValue, isolate_)),
3553  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3554  SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3555  break;
3556  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined:
3557  result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
3558  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value()),
3559  ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ ObjectIs(
3560  input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable,
3561  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone)),
3562  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3563  SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3564  break;
3565  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kObject:
3566  result = __ Select(__ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable,
3567  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone),
3568  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value()),
3569  ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ RootEqual(
3570  input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_)),
3571  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3572  SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3573  break;
3574  case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kOther:
3575  UNREACHABLE(); // Should never be emitted.
3576  }
3577 
3578  SetMap(node, result);
3579  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3580  }

3692 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3693  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::BranchIfFloat64IsUndefinedOrHole* node,
3694  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3695  V<Float64> input = Map(node->condition_input());
3696  V<Word32> undefined_condition = __ Float64IsUndefined(input);
3697  __ GotoIf(undefined_condition, Map(node->if_true()));
3698  V<Word32> hole_condition = __ Float64IsHole(Map(node->condition_input()));
3699  __ Branch(hole_condition, Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3700  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3701  }
3702 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3703  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::BranchIfReferenceEqual* node,
3704  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3705  V<Word32> condition =
3706  __ TaggedEqual(Map(node->left_input()), Map(node->right_input()));
3707  __ Branch(condition, Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3708  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3709  }

3711  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3712  V<Word32> condition =
3713  RootEqual(node->condition_input(), node->root_index());
3714  __ Branch(condition, Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3715  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3716  }
3717  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::BranchIfUndefinedOrNull* node,
3718  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3719  __ GotoIf(RootEqual(node->condition_input(), RootIndex::kUndefinedValue),
3720  Map(node->if_true()));
3721  __ Branch(RootEqual(node->condition_input(), RootIndex::kNullValue),
3722  Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3723  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3724  }
3725  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::BranchIfUndetectable* node,
3726  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3727  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions assumption;
3728  switch (node->check_type()) {
3729  case maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject:
3730  assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone;
3731  break;
3732  case maglev::CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck:
3733  assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject;
3734  break;
3735  }
3736  __ Branch(__ ObjectIs(Map(node->condition_input()),
3737  ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable, assumption),
3738  Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3739  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3740  }

3744  Map(node->if_false()));
3745  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3746  }

3748  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3749  __ GotoIf(__ IsSmi(Map(node->condition_input())), Map(node->if_false()));
3750  __ Branch(__ JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Map(node->condition_input())),
3751  Map(node->if_true()), Map(node->if_false()));
3752  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3753  }
3754 
3755  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Switch* node,
3756  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3757  if (is_visiting_generator_main_switch_) {
3758  // This is the main resume-switch for a generator, and some of its target
3759  // bypass loop headers. We need to re-route the destinations to the
3760  // bypassed loop headers, where secondary switches will be inserted.
3761 
3762  compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
3763  __ output_graph().graph_zone()
3764  -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
3765  node->size());
3766 
3767  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->value_base());
3768 
3769  for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
3770  maglev::BasicBlock* target = node->targets()[i].block_ptr();
3771  if (generator_analyzer_.JumpBypassesHeader(target)) {
3772  Block* new_dst = __ NewBlock();
3773 
3774  const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_bypassed_header =
3775  generator_analyzer_.GetInnermostBypassedHeader(target);
3776 
3777  pre_loop_generator_blocks_[innermost_bypassed_header].push_back(
3778  {new_dst, Map(target), i});
3779 
3780  // {innermost_bypassed_header} is only the innermost bypassed header.
3781  // We also need to record bypasses of outer headers. In the end, we
3782  // want this main Switch to go to before the outermost header, which
3783  // will dispatch to the next inner loop, and so on until the innermost
3784  // loop header and then to the initial destination.
3785  for (const maglev::BasicBlock* bypassed_header =
3786  generator_analyzer_.GetLoopHeader(innermost_bypassed_header);
3787  bypassed_header != nullptr;
3788  bypassed_header =
3789  generator_analyzer_.GetLoopHeader(bypassed_header)) {
3790  Block* prev_loop_dst = __ NewBlock();
3791  pre_loop_generator_blocks_[bypassed_header].push_back(
3792  {prev_loop_dst, new_dst, i});
3793  new_dst = prev_loop_dst;
3794  }
3795 
3796  cases[i] = {i, new_dst, BranchHint::kNone};
3797 
3798  } else {
3799  cases[i] = {i, Map(target), BranchHint::kNone};
3800  }
3801  }
3802 
3803  Block* default_block = __ NewBlock();
3804  __ Switch(Map(node->value()), base::VectorOf(cases, node->size()),
3805  default_block);
3806  __ Bind(default_block);
3807  __ Unreachable();
3808 
3809  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3810  }
3811 
3812  compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
3813  __ output_graph().graph_zone()
3814  -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
3815  node->size());
3816  int case_value_base = node->value_base();
3817  for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
3818  cases[i] = {i + case_value_base, Map(node->targets()[i].block_ptr()),
3819  BranchHint::kNone};
3820  }
3821  Block* default_block;
3822  bool emit_default_block = false;
3823  if (node->has_fallthrough()) {
3824  default_block = Map(state.next_block());
3825  } else {
3826  default_block = __ NewBlock();
3827  emit_default_block = true;
3828  }
3829  __ Switch(Map(node->value()), base::VectorOf(cases, node->size()),
3830  default_block);
3831  if (emit_default_block) {
3832  __ Bind(default_block);
3833  __ Unreachable();
3834  }
3835  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3836  }

4023 #define PROCESS_INT32_SHIFT(MaglevName, TurboshaftName) \
4024  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32##MaglevName* node, \
4025  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) { \
4026  V<Word32> right = Map(node->right_input()); \
4027  if (!SupportedOperations::word32_shift_is_safe()) { \
4028  /* JavaScript spec says that the right-hand side of a shift should be \
4029  * taken modulo 32. Some architectures do this automatically, some \
4030  * don't. For those that don't, which do this modulo 32 with a `& 0x1f`. \
4031  */ \
4032  right = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(right, 0x1f); \
4033  } \
4034  SetMap(node, __ Word32##TurboshaftName(Map(node->left_input()), right)); \
4035  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue; \
4036  }

4041  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32ShiftRightLogical* node,
4042  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {

4044  if (!SupportedOperations::word32_shift_is_safe()) {
4045  // JavaScript spec says that the right-hand side of a shift should be
4046  // taken modulo 32. Some architectures do this automatically, some
4047  // don't. For those that don't, which do this modulo 32 with a `& 0x1f`.
4048  right = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(right, 0x1f);
4049  }
4050  V<Word32> ts_op =

4052  SetMap(node, __ Word32SignHintUnsigned(ts_op));

4063  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32AbsWithOverflow* node,
4064  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4065  V<Word32> input = Map(node->input());
4066  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4067  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this, input);
4068 
4069  IF (__ Int32LessThan(input, 0)) {
4070  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> result_with_ovf =
4071  __ Int32MulCheckOverflow(input, -1);
4072  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Projection<1>(result_with_ovf), frame_state,
4073  DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
4074  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
4075  result = __ Projection<0>(result_with_ovf);
4076  }
4077 
4078  SetMap(node, result);
4079  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4080  }

4092  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64Round* node,
4093  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4094  if (node->kind() == maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kFloor) {
4095  SetMap(node, __ Float64RoundDown(Map(node->input())));
4096  } else if (node->kind() == maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kCeil) {
4097  SetMap(node, __ Float64RoundUp(Map(node->input())));
4098  } else {
4099  DCHECK_EQ(node->kind(), maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kNearest);
4100  // Nearest rounds to +infinity on ties. We emulate this by rounding up and
4101  // adjusting if the difference exceeds 0.5 (like SimplifiedLowering does
4102  // for lower Float64Round).
4103  OpIndex input = Map(node->input());
4104  ScopedVar<Float64, AssemblerT> result(this, __ Float64RoundUp(input));
4105  IF_NOT (__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(__ Float64Sub(result, 0.5), input)) {
4106  result = __ Float64Sub(result, 1.0);
4107  }
4108 
4109  SetMap(node, result);
4110  }
4111  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4112  }

4114  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64Ieee754Unary* node,
4115  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4116  FloatUnaryOp::Kind kind;
4117  switch (node->ieee_function()) {
4118 #define CASE(MathName, ExpName, EnumName) \
4119  case maglev::Float64Ieee754Unary::Ieee754Function::k##EnumName: \
4120  kind = FloatUnaryOp::Kind::k##EnumName; \
4121  break;
4122  IEEE_754_UNARY_LIST(CASE)
4123 #undef CASE
4124  }
4125  SetMap(node, __ Float64Unary(Map(node->input()), kind));
4126  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4127  }

4129  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedSmiIncrement* node,
4130  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4131  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4132  V<Smi> result;
4133  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
4134  result = __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ Word32SignedAddDeoptOnOverflow(
4135  __ BitcastSmiToWord32(Map(node->value_input())),
4136  Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
4137  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4138  } else {
4139  // Remember that 32-bit Smis are stored in the upper 32 bits of 64-bit
4140  // qwords. We thus perform a 64-bit addition rather than a 32-bit one,
4141  // despite Smis being only 32 bits.
4142  result = __ BitcastWordPtrToSmi(__ WordPtrSignedAddDeoptOnOverflow(
4143  __ BitcastSmiToWordPtr(Map(node->value_input())),
4144  Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
4145  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4146  }
4147  SetMap(node, result);
4148  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4149  }
4150  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedSmiDecrement* node,
4151  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4152  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4153  V<Smi> result;
4154  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
4155  result = __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ Word32SignedSubDeoptOnOverflow(
4156  __ BitcastSmiToWord32(Map(node->value_input())),
4157  Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
4158  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4159  } else {
4160  result = __ BitcastWordPtrToSmi(__ WordPtrSignedSubDeoptOnOverflow(
4161  __ BitcastSmiToWordPtr(Map(node->value_input())),
4162  Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
4163  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4164  }
4165  SetMap(node, result);
4166  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4167  }

4169 // Note that Maglev collects feedback in the generic binops and unops, so that
4170 // Turbofan has chance to get better feedback. However, once we reach Turbofan,
4171 // we stop collecting feedback, since we've tried multiple times to keep
4172 // collecting feedback in Turbofan, but it never seemed worth it. The latest
4173 // occurence of this was ended by this CL: https://crrev.com/c/4110858.
4174 #define PROCESS_GENERIC_BINOP(Name) \
4175  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Generic##Name* node, \
4176  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) { \

4311  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64* node,
4312  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4313  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4314  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind;
4315  switch (node->conversion_type()) {
4316  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
4317  kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber;
4318  break;
4319  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean:
4320  kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
4321  kNumberOrBoolean;
4322  break;
4323  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
4324  kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
4325  kNumberOrOddball;
4326  break;

4329  __ ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4330  Map(node->input()), frame_state, kind,
4331  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64,
4332  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
4333  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4334  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4335  }

4428  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedObjectToIndex* node,
4429  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4430  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4431  const FeedbackSource& feedback =
4432  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update();
4433  OpIndex result = __ ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4434  Map(node->object_input()), frame_state,
4435  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumberOrString,
4436  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kArrayIndex,
4437  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero, feedback);
4438  if constexpr (Is64()) {
4439  // ArrayIndex is 32-bit in Maglev, but 64 in Turboshaft. This means that
4440  // we have to convert it to 32-bit before the following `SetMap`, and we
4441  // thus have to check that it actually fits in a Uint32.
4442  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
4443  result, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()),
4444  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32, feedback);
4445  RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
4446  }
4447  SetMap(node, Is64() ? __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(result) : result);
4448  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4449  }

4485  maglev::ProcessResult Process(
4486  maglev::CheckedTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32* node,
4487  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4488  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement input_requirement;
4489  switch (node->conversion_type()) {
4490  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
4491  input_requirement =
4492  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement::kNumber;
4493  break;
4494  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean:
4495  input_requirement = TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
4496  InputRequirement::kNumberOrBoolean;
4497  break;
4498  case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
4499  input_requirement = TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
4500  InputRequirement::kNumberOrOddball;
4501  break;
4502  }
4503  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4504  SetMap(
4505  node,
4506  __ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4507  Map(node->input()), frame_state,
4508  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32,
4509  input_requirement, node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4510  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4511  }
4512  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32* node,
4513  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4514  // In Maglev, TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32 does the same thing for both
4515  // NumberOrOddball and Number; except when debug_code is enabled: then,
4516  // Maglev inserts runtime checks ensuring that the input is indeed a Number
4517  // or NumberOrOddball. Turboshaft doesn't typically introduce such runtime
4518  // checks, so we instead just lower both Number and NumberOrOddball to the
4519  // NumberOrOddball variant.
4520  SetMap(node, __ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged(
4521  Map(node->input()),
4522  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32,
4523  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::
4524  kNumberOrOddball));
4525  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4526  }

4556  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedHoleyFloat64ToFloat64* node,
4557  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4558  V<Float64> input = Map(node->input());

4568  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConvertHoleToUndefined* node,
4569  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4570  V<Word32> cond = RootEqual(node->object_input(), RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
4571  SetMap(node,
4572  __ Select(cond, undefined_value_, Map<Object>(node->object_input()),
4573  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
4574  SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch));
4575  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4576  }
4577  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConvertReceiver* node,
4578  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4579  NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);
4580 
4581  Label<Object> done(this);
4582  Label<> non_js_receiver(this);
4583  V<Object> receiver = Map(node->receiver_input());
4584 
4585  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(receiver), non_js_receiver);
4586 
4587  GOTO_IF(__ JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(V<HeapObject>::Cast(receiver)), done,
4588  receiver);
4589 
4590  if (node->mode() != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
4591  Label<> convert_global_proxy(this);
4592  GOTO_IF(__ RootEqual(receiver, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, isolate_),
4593  convert_global_proxy);
4594  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ RootEqual(receiver, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
4595  non_js_receiver);
4596  GOTO(convert_global_proxy);
4597  BIND(convert_global_proxy);
4598  GOTO(done,
4599  __ HeapConstant(
4600  node->native_context().global_proxy_object(broker_).object()));
4601  } else {
4602  GOTO(non_js_receiver);
4603  }
4604 
4605  BIND(non_js_receiver);
4606  GOTO(done, __ CallBuiltin_ToObject(
4607  isolate_, __ HeapConstant(node->native_context().object()),
4608  V<JSPrimitive>::Cast(receiver)));
4609 
4610  BIND(done, result);
4611  SetMap(node, result);
4612 
4613  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4614  }
4615 
4616  static constexpr int kMinClampedUint8 = 0;
4617  static constexpr int kMaxClampedUint8 = 255;
4618  V<Word32> Int32ToUint8Clamped(V<Word32> value) {
4619  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4620  IF (__ Int32LessThan(value, kMinClampedUint8)) {
4621  result = __ Word32Constant(kMinClampedUint8);
4622  } ELSE IF (__ Int32LessThan(value, kMaxClampedUint8)) {
4623  result = value;
4624  } ELSE {
4625  result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4626  }
4627  return result;
4628  }
4629  V<Word32> Float64ToUint8Clamped(V<Float64> value) {
4630  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4631  IF (__ Float64LessThan(value, kMinClampedUint8)) {
4632  result = __ Word32Constant(kMinClampedUint8);
4633  } ELSE IF (__ Float64LessThan(kMaxClampedUint8, value)) {
4634  result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4635  } ELSE {
4636  // Note that this case handles values that are in range of Clamped Uint8
4637  // and NaN. The order of the IF/ELSE-IF/ELSE in this function is so that
4638  // we do indeed end up here for NaN.
4639  result = __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(__ Float64RoundTiesEven(value));
4640  }
4641  return result;
4642  }
4643 
4644  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32ToUint8Clamped* node,
4645  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4646  SetMap(node, Int32ToUint8Clamped(Map(node->input())));
4647  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4648  }
4649  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Uint32ToUint8Clamped* node,
4650  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4651  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4652  V<Word32> value = Map(node->input());
4653  IF (__ Uint32LessThan(value, kMaxClampedUint8)) {
4654  result = value;
4655  } ELSE {
4656  result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4657  }
4658  SetMap(node, result);
4659  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4660  }
4661  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64ToUint8Clamped* node,
4662  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4663  SetMap(node, Float64ToUint8Clamped(Map(node->input())));
4664  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4665  }
4666  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped* node,
4667  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4668  ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4669  V<Object> value = Map(node->input());
4670  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4671  IF (__ IsSmi(value)) {
4672  result = Int32ToUint8Clamped(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(value)));
4673  } ELSE {
4674  V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(value);
4675  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
4676  __ TaggedEqual(map,
4677  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->heap_number_map())),
4678  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber,
4679  node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
4680  result = Float64ToUint8Clamped(
4681  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(value)));
4682  }
4683  RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
4684  SetMap(node, result);
4685  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4686  }

4688  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ToObject* node,
4689  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4690  GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
4691  OpIndex arguments[] = {Map(node->value_input()), Map(node->context())};
4692 
4693  GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, Builtin::kToObject, frame_state,
4694  base::VectorOf(arguments));
4695 
4696  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4697  }

4713  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::SetPendingMessage* node,
4714  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {

4716  ExternalReference::address_of_pending_message(isolate_));
4717  V<Object> old_message = __ LoadMessage(message_address);
4718  __ StoreMessage(message_address, Map(node->value()));

4723  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::GeneratorStore* node,
4724  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4725  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 32> parameters_and_registers;
4726  int num_parameters_and_registers = node->num_parameters_and_registers();
4727  for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers; i++) {
4728  parameters_and_registers.push_back(
4729  Map(node->parameters_and_registers(i)));
4730  }
4731  __ GeneratorStore(Map(node->context_input()), Map(node->generator_input()),
4732  parameters_and_registers, node->suspend_id(),
4733  node->bytecode_offset());
4734  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4735  }
4736  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::GeneratorRestoreRegister* node,
4737  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4738  V<FixedArray> array = Map(node->array_input());
4739  V<Object> result =
4740  __ LoadTaggedField(array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(node->index()));
4741  __ Store(array, Map(node->stale_input()), StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
4742  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
4743  WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
4744  FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(node->index()));
4745 
4746  SetMap(node, result);
4747 
4748  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4749  }

4849 
4850  maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AssertInt32* node,
4851  const maglev::ProcessingState&) {
4852  bool negate_result = false;
4853  V<Word32> cmp = ConvertInt32Compare(node->left_input(), node->right_input(),
4854  node->condition(), &negate_result);
4855  Label<> abort(this);
4856  Label<> end(this);
4857  if (negate_result) {
4858  GOTO_IF(cmp, abort);
4859  } else {
4860  GOTO_IF_NOT(cmp, abort);
4861  }
4862  GOTO(end);
4863 
4864  BIND(abort);
4865  __ RuntimeAbort(node->reason());
4866  __ Unreachable();
4867 
4868  BIND(end);
4869  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4870  }

4876  // Turboshaft).
4877  UNREACHABLE();
4878  }

4909  private:
4910  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4911  maglev::EagerDeoptInfo* eager_deopt_info) {
4912  deduplicator_.Reset();
4913  // Eager deopts don't have a result location/size.
4914  const interpreter::Register result_location =
4915  interpreter::Register::invalid_value();
4916  const int result_size = 0;
4917  const maglev::VirtualObjectList virtual_objects =
4918  eager_deopt_info->top_frame().GetVirtualObjects();
4919 
4920  switch (eager_deopt_info->top_frame().type()) {
4921  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4922  return BuildFrameState(eager_deopt_info->top_frame().as_interpreted(),
4923  virtual_objects, result_location, result_size);
4924  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4925  return BuildFrameState(
4926  eager_deopt_info->top_frame().as_builtin_continuation(),
4927  virtual_objects);
4928  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4929  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4930  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4931  }
4932  }
4933 
4934  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4935  maglev::LazyDeoptInfo* lazy_deopt_info) {
4936  deduplicator_.Reset();
4937  const maglev::VirtualObjectList virtual_objects =
4938  lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().GetVirtualObjects();
4939  switch (lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().type()) {
4940  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4941  return BuildFrameState(
4942  lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_interpreted(), virtual_objects,
4943  lazy_deopt_info->result_location(), lazy_deopt_info->result_size());
4944  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4945  return BuildFrameState(lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_construct_stub(),
4946  virtual_objects);
4947 
4948  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4949  return BuildFrameState(
4950  lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_builtin_continuation(),
4951  virtual_objects);
4952 
4953  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4954  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4955  }
4956  }
4957 
4958  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildParentFrameState(
4959  maglev::DeoptFrame& frame,
4960  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects) {
4961  // Only the topmost frame should have a valid result_location and
4962  // result_size. One reason for this is that, in Maglev, the PokeAt is not an
4963  // attribute of the DeoptFrame but rather of the LazyDeoptInfo (to which the
4964  // topmost frame is attached).
4965  const interpreter::Register result_location =
4966  interpreter::Register::invalid_value();
4967  const int result_size = 0;
4968 
4969  switch (frame.type()) {
4970  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4971  return BuildFrameState(frame.as_interpreted(), virtual_objects,
4972  result_location, result_size);
4973  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4974  return BuildFrameState(frame.as_construct_stub(), virtual_objects);
4975  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4976  return BuildFrameState(frame.as_inlined_arguments(), virtual_objects);
4977  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4978  return BuildFrameState(frame.as_builtin_continuation(),
4979  virtual_objects);
4980  }
4981  }
4982 
4983  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4984  maglev::ConstructInvokeStubDeoptFrame& frame,
4985  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects) {
4986  FrameStateData::Builder builder;
4987  if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
4988  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
4989  BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
4990  if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4991  builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
4992  }
4993 
4994  // Closure
4995  // TODO(dmercadier): ConstructInvokeStub frames don't have a Closure input,
4996  // but the instruction selector assumes that they do and that it should be
4997  // skipped. We thus use SmiConstant(0) as a fake Closure input here, but it
4998  // would be nicer to fix the instruction selector to not require this input
4999  // at all for such frames.
5000  V<Any> fake_closure_input = __ SmiZeroConstant();
5001  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), fake_closure_input);
5002 
5003  // Parameters
5004  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.receiver());
5005 
5006  // Context
5007  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.context());
5008 
5009  if (builder.Inputs().size() >
5010  std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
5011  *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
5012  return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5013  }
5014 
5015  const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
5016  return __ FrameState(
5017  builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
5018  builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
5019  }
5020 
5021  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
5022  maglev::InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame& frame,
5023  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects) {
5024  FrameStateData::Builder builder;
5025  if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
5026  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
5027  BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
5028  if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5029  builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
5030  }
5031 
5032  // Closure
5033  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.closure());
5034 
5035  // Parameters
5036  for (const maglev::ValueNode* arg : frame.arguments()) {
5037  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, arg);
5038  }
5039 
5040  // Context
5041  // TODO(dmercadier): InlinedExtraArguments frames don't have a Context
5042  // input, but the instruction selector assumes that they do and that it
5043  // should be skipped. We thus use SmiConstant(0) as a fake Context input
5044  // here, but it would be nicer to fix the instruction selector to not
5045  // require this input at all for such frames.
5046  V<Any> fake_context_input = __ SmiZeroConstant();
5047  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), fake_context_input);
5048 
5049  if (builder.Inputs().size() >
5050  std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
5051  *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
5052  return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5053  }
5054 
5055  const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
5056  return __ FrameState(
5057  builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
5058  builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
5059  }
5060 
5061  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
5062  maglev::BuiltinContinuationDeoptFrame& frame,
5063  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects) {
5064  FrameStateData::Builder builder;
5065  if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
5066  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
5067  BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
5068  if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5069  builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
5070  }
5071 
5072  // Closure
5073  if (frame.is_javascript()) {
5074  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5075  __ HeapConstant(frame.javascript_target().object()));
5076  } else {
5077  builder.AddUnusedRegister();
5078  }
5079 
5080  // Parameters
5081  for (maglev::ValueNode* param : frame.parameters()) {
5082  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, param);
5083  }
5084 
5085  // Extra fixed JS frame parameters. These are at the end since JS builtins
5086  // push their parameters in reverse order.
5087  constexpr int kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters =
5088  V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL ? 4 : 3;
5089  if (frame.is_javascript()) {
5090  DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id())
5091  .GetRegisterParameterCount(),
5092  kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters);
5093  static_assert(kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters ==
5094  3 + (V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL ? 1 : 0));
5095  // kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister
5096  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5097  __ HeapConstant(frame.javascript_target().object()));
5098  // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister
5099  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), undefined_value_);
5100  // kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister
5101  builder.AddInput(
5102  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5103  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(
5104  Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id()))));
5105 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
5106  // kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister
5107  builder.AddInput(
5108  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5109  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(kInvalidDispatchHandle.value())));
5110 #endif
5111  }
5112 
5113  // Context
5114  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.context());
5115 
5116  if (builder.Inputs().size() >
5117  std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
5118  *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
5119  return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5120  }
5121 
5122  const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
5123  return __ FrameState(
5124  builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
5125  builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
5126  }
5127 
5128  OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
5129  maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& frame,
5130  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects,
5131  interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
5132  DCHECK_EQ(result_size != 0, result_location.is_valid());
5133  FrameStateData::Builder builder;
5134 
5135  if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
5136  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
5137  BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
5138  if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5139  builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
5140  }
5141 
5142  // Closure
5143  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.closure());
5144 
5145  // Parameters
5146  frame.frame_state()->ForEachParameter(
5147  frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
5148  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value, reg, result_location,
5149  result_size);
5150  });
5151 
5152  // Context
5153  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects,
5154  frame.frame_state()->context(frame.unit()));
5155 
5156  // Locals
5157  // ForEachLocal in Maglev skips over dead registers, but we still need to
5158  // call AddUnusedRegister on the Turboshaft FrameStateData Builder.
5159  // {local_index} is used to keep track of such unused registers.
5160  // Among the variables not included in ForEachLocal is the Accumulator (but
5161  // this is fine since there is an entry in the state specifically for the
5162  // accumulator later).
5163  int local_index = 0;
5164  frame.frame_state()->ForEachLocal(
5165  frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
5166  while (local_index < reg.index()) {
5167  builder.AddUnusedRegister();
5168  local_index++;
5169  }
5170  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value, reg, result_location,
5171  result_size);
5172  local_index++;
5173  });
5174  for (; local_index < frame.unit().register_count(); local_index++) {
5175  builder.AddUnusedRegister();
5176  }
5177 
5178  // Accumulator
5179  if (frame.frame_state()->liveness()->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
5180  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects,
5181  frame.frame_state()->accumulator(frame.unit()),
5182  interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
5183  result_location, result_size);
5184  } else {
5185  builder.AddUnusedRegister();
5186  }
5187 
5188  OutputFrameStateCombine combine =
5189  ComputeCombine(frame, result_location, result_size);
5190 
5191  if (builder.Inputs().size() >
5192  std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
5193  *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
5194  return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
5195  }
5196 
5197  const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame, combine);
5198  return __ FrameState(
5199  builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
5200  builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
5201  }
5202 
5203  void AddDeoptInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
5204  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects,
5205  const maglev::ValueNode* node) {
5206  while (node->Is<maglev::Identity>()) {
5207  node = node->input(0).node();
5208  }
5209  if (const maglev::InlinedAllocation* alloc =
5210  node->TryCast<maglev::InlinedAllocation>()) {
5211  DCHECK(alloc->HasBeenAnalysed());
5212  if (alloc->HasBeenElided()) {
5213  AddVirtualObjectInput(builder, virtual_objects,
5214  virtual_objects.FindAllocatedWith(alloc));
5215  return;
5216  }
5217  }
5218  builder.AddInput(MachineTypeFor(node->value_representation()), Map(node));
5219  }
5220 
5221  void AddDeoptInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
5222  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects,
5223  const maglev::ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register reg,
5224  interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
5225  if (result_location.is_valid() && maglev::LazyDeoptInfo::InReturnValues(
5226  reg, result_location, result_size)) {
5227  builder.AddUnusedRegister();
5228  } else {
5229  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, node);
5230  }
5231  }
5232 
5233  void AddVirtualObjectInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
5234  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects,
5235  const maglev::VirtualObject* vobj) {
5236  if (vobj->type() == maglev::VirtualObject::kHeapNumber) {
5237  // We need to add HeapNumbers as dematerialized HeapNumbers (rather than
5238  // simply NumberConstant), because they could be mutable HeapNumber
5239  // fields, in which case we don't want GVN to merge them.
5240  constexpr int kNumberOfField = 2; // map + value
5241  builder.AddDematerializedObject(deduplicator_.CreateUnduplicatableId().id,
5242  kNumberOfField);
5243  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5244  __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->heap_number_map()));
5245  builder.AddInput(MachineType::Float64(),
5246  __ Float64Constant(vobj->number()));
5247  return;
5248  }
5249 
5250  Deduplicator::DuplicatedId dup_id = deduplicator_.GetDuplicatedId(vobj);
5251  if (dup_id.duplicated) {
5252  builder.AddDematerializedObjectReference(dup_id.id);
5253  return;
5254  }
5255 
5256  switch (vobj->type()) {
5257  case maglev::VirtualObject::kHeapNumber:
5258  // Handled above
5259  UNREACHABLE();
5260  case maglev::VirtualObject::kConsString:
5261  // TODO(olivf): Support elided maglev cons strings in turbolev.
5262  UNREACHABLE();
5263  case maglev::VirtualObject::kFixedDoubleArray: {
5264  constexpr int kMapAndLengthFieldCount = 2;
5265  uint32_t length = vobj->double_elements_length();
5266  uint32_t field_count = length + kMapAndLengthFieldCount;
5267  builder.AddDematerializedObject(dup_id.id, field_count);
5268  builder.AddInput(
5269  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5270  __ HeapConstantNoHole(local_factory_->fixed_double_array_map()));
5271  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5272  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(length)));
5273  FixedDoubleArrayRef elements = vobj->double_elements();
5274  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5275  i::Float64 value = elements.GetFromImmutableFixedDoubleArray(i);
5276  if (value.is_hole_nan()) {
5277  builder.AddInput(
5278  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5279  __ HeapConstantHole(local_factory_->the_hole_value()));
5280  } else {
5281  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5282  __ NumberConstant(value.get_scalar()));
5283  }
5284  }
5285  return;
5286  }
5287  case maglev::VirtualObject::kDefault:
5288  constexpr int kMapFieldCount = 1;
5289  uint32_t field_count = vobj->slot_count() + kMapFieldCount;
5290  builder.AddDematerializedObject(dup_id.id, field_count);
5291  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5292  __ HeapConstantNoHole(vobj->map().object()));
5293  vobj->ForEachInput([&](maglev::ValueNode* value_node) {
5294  AddVirtualObjectNestedValue(builder, virtual_objects, value_node);
5295  });
5296  break;
5297  }
5298  }
5299 
5300  void AddVirtualObjectNestedValue(
5301  FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
5302  const maglev::VirtualObjectList& virtual_objects,
5303  const maglev::ValueNode* value) {
5304  if (maglev::IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
5305  switch (value->opcode()) {
5306  case maglev::Opcode::kConstant:
5307  builder.AddInput(
5308  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5309  __ HeapConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Constant>()->ref().object()));
5310  break;
5311 
5312  case maglev::Opcode::kFloat64Constant:
5313  builder.AddInput(
5314  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5315  __ NumberConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Float64Constant>()
5316  ->value()
5317  .get_scalar()));
5318  break;
5319 
5320  case maglev::Opcode::kInt32Constant:
5321  builder.AddInput(
5322  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5323  __ NumberConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Int32Constant>()->value()));
5324  break;
5325 
5326  case maglev::Opcode::kUint32Constant:
5327  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5328  __ NumberConstant(
5329  value->Cast<maglev::Uint32Constant>()->value()));
5330  break;
5331 
5332  case maglev::Opcode::kIntPtrConstant:
5333  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5334  __ NumberConstant(
5335  value->Cast<maglev::IntPtrConstant>()->value()));
5336  break;
5337 
5338  case maglev::Opcode::kRootConstant:
5339  builder.AddInput(
5340  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5341  (__ HeapConstant(Cast<HeapObject>(isolate_->root_handle(
5342  value->Cast<maglev::RootConstant>()->index())))));
5343  break;
5344 
5345  case maglev::Opcode::kSmiConstant:
5346  builder.AddInput(
5347  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5348  __ SmiConstant(value->Cast<maglev::SmiConstant>()->value()));
5349  break;
5350 
5351  case maglev::Opcode::kTrustedConstant:
5352  builder.AddInput(
5353  MachineType::AnyTagged(),
5354  __ TrustedHeapConstant(
5355  value->Cast<maglev::TrustedConstant>()->object().object()));
5356  break;
5357 
5358  case maglev::Opcode::kTaggedIndexConstant:
5359  default:
5360  UNREACHABLE();
5361  }
5362  return;
5363  }
5364 
5365  // Special nodes.
5366  switch (value->opcode()) {
5367  case maglev::Opcode::kArgumentsElements:
5368  builder.AddArgumentsElements(
5369  value->Cast<maglev::ArgumentsElements>()->type());
5370  break;
5371  case maglev::Opcode::kArgumentsLength:
5372  builder.AddArgumentsLength();
5373  break;
5374  case maglev::Opcode::kRestLength:
5375  builder.AddRestLength();
5376  break;
5377  case maglev::Opcode::kVirtualObject:
5378  UNREACHABLE();
5379  default:
5380  AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value);
5381  break;
5382  }
5383  }
5384 
5385  class Deduplicator {
5386  public:
5387  struct DuplicatedId {
5388  uint32_t id;
5389  bool duplicated;
5390  };
5391  DuplicatedId GetDuplicatedId(const maglev::VirtualObject* object) {
5392  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(object);
5393  // TODO(dmercadier): do better than a linear search here.
5394  for (uint32_t idx = 0; idx < object_ids_.size(); idx++) {
5395  if (object_ids_[idx] == object) {
5396  return {idx, true};
5397  }
5398  }
5399  return CreateFreshId(object);
5400  }
5401 
5402  DuplicatedId CreateUnduplicatableId() { return CreateFreshId(nullptr); }
5403 
5404  void Reset() { object_ids_.clear(); }
5405 
5406  private:
5407  DuplicatedId CreateFreshId(const maglev::VirtualObject* object) {
5408  uint32_t next_id = static_cast<uint32_t>(object_ids_.size());
5409  object_ids_.push_back(object);
5410  return {next_id, false};
5411  }
5412 
5413  std::vector<const maglev::VirtualObject*> object_ids_;
5414  };
5415 
5416  OutputFrameStateCombine ComputeCombine(maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& frame,
5417  interpreter::Register result_location,
5418  int result_size) {
5419  if (result_size == 0) {
5420  return OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore();
5421  }
5422  return OutputFrameStateCombine::PokeAt(
5423  frame.ComputeReturnOffset(result_location, result_size));
5424  }

5431  uint16_t max_arguments = maglev_frame.unit().max_arguments();
5432  int local_count = maglev_frame.unit().register_count();

5434  maglev_frame.unit().shared_function_info().object();
5435  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array =
5436  maglev_frame.unit().bytecode().object();
5437  FrameStateFunctionInfo* info = graph_zone()->New<FrameStateFunctionInfo>(
5438  type, parameter_count, max_arguments, local_count, shared_info,
5439  bytecode_array);
5440 
5441  return graph_zone()->New<FrameStateInfo>(maglev_frame.bytecode_position(),
5442  combine, info);
5443  }

5483  const FrameStateInfo* MakeFrameStateInfo(
5484  maglev::BuiltinContinuationDeoptFrame& maglev_frame) {
5485  FrameStateType type = maglev_frame.is_javascript()
5486  ? FrameStateType::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation
5487  : FrameStateType::kBuiltinContinuation;
5488  uint16_t parameter_count =
5489  static_cast<uint16_t>(maglev_frame.parameters().length());
5490  if (maglev_frame.is_javascript()) {
5491  constexpr int kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters =
5492  V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL ? 4 : 3;
5493  DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(maglev_frame.builtin_id())
5494  .GetRegisterParameterCount(),
5495  kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters);
5496  parameter_count += kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters;
5497  }
5498  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
5499  GetSharedFunctionInfo(maglev_frame).object();
5500  constexpr int kLocalCount = 0;
5501  constexpr uint16_t kMaxArguments = 0;
5502  FrameStateFunctionInfo* info = graph_zone()->New<FrameStateFunctionInfo>(
5503  type, parameter_count, kMaxArguments, kLocalCount, shared_info,
5504  kNullMaybeHandle);
5505 
5506  return graph_zone()->New<FrameStateInfo>(
5507  Builtins::GetContinuationBytecodeOffset(maglev_frame.builtin_id()),
5508  OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), info);
5509  }

5511  SharedFunctionInfoRef GetSharedFunctionInfo(
5512  const maglev::DeoptFrame& deopt_frame) {
5513  switch (deopt_frame.type()) {
5514  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
5515  return deopt_frame.as_interpreted().unit().shared_function_info();
5516  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
5517  return deopt_frame.as_inlined_arguments().unit().shared_function_info();
5518  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
5519  return deopt_frame.as_construct_stub().unit().shared_function_info();
5520  case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
5521  return GetSharedFunctionInfo(*deopt_frame.parent());
5522  }
5523  UNREACHABLE();
5524  }
5525 
5526  enum class Sign { kSigned, kUnsigned };
5527  template <typename rep>
5528  V<Word32> ConvertCompare(maglev::Input left_input, maglev::Input right_input,
5529  ::Operation operation, Sign sign) {
5530  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
5531  (std::is_same_v<rep, Float64> || std::is_same_v<rep, Float32>),
5532  sign == Sign::kSigned);
5533  ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
5534  bool swap_inputs = false;
5535  switch (operation) {
5536  case ::Operation::kEqual:
5537  case ::Operation::kStrictEqual:
5538  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5539  break;
5540  case ::Operation::kLessThan:
5541  kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
5542  : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5543  break;
5544  case ::Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
5545  kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
5546  ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
5547  : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5548  break;
5549  case ::Operation::kGreaterThan:
5550  kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
5551  : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5552  swap_inputs = true;
5553  break;
5554  case ::Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
5555  kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
5556  ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
5557  : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5558  swap_inputs = true;
5559  break;
5560  default:
5561  UNREACHABLE();
5562  }
5563  V<rep> left = Map(left_input);
5564  V<rep> right = Map(right_input);
5565  if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
5566  return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, V<rep>::rep);
5567  }
5568 
5569  V<Word32> ConvertInt32Compare(maglev::Input left_input,
5570  maglev::Input right_input,
5571  maglev::AssertCondition condition,
5572  bool* negate_result) {
5573  ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
5574  bool swap_inputs = false;
5575  switch (condition) {
5576  case maglev::AssertCondition::kEqual:
5577  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5578  break;
5579  case maglev::AssertCondition::kNotEqual:
5580  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5581  *negate_result = true;
5582  break;
5583  case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThan:
5584  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
5585  break;
5586  case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual:
5587  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
5588  break;
5589  case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThan:
5590  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
5591  swap_inputs = true;
5592  break;
5593  case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThanEqual:
5594  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
5595  swap_inputs = true;
5596  break;
5597  case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan:
5598  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5599  break;
5600  case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
5601  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5602  break;
5603  case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThan:
5604  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5605  swap_inputs = true;
5606  break;
5607  case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
5608  kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5609  swap_inputs = true;
5610  break;
5611  }
5612  V<Word32> left = Map(left_input);
5613  V<Word32> right = Map(right_input);
5614  if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
5615  return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, WordRepresentation::Word32());
5616  }
5617 
5618  V<Word32> RootEqual(maglev::Input input, RootIndex root) {
5619  return __ RootEqual(Map(input), root, isolate_);
5620  }

5622  void DeoptIfInt32IsNotSmi(maglev::Input maglev_input,

5628  void DeoptIfInt32IsNotSmi(V<Word32> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
5629  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback) {
5630  // TODO(dmercadier): is there no higher level way of doing this?
5631  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> add = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(input, input);
5632  V<Word32> check = __ template Projection<1>(add);
5633  __ DeoptimizeIf(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, feedback);
5634  }

5636  std::pair<V<WordPtr>, V<Object>> GetTypedArrayDataAndBasePointers(
5637  V<JSTypedArray> typed_array) {
5638  V<WordPtr> data_pointer = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
5639  typed_array, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer());
5640  V<Object> base_pointer = __ LoadField<Object>(
5641  typed_array, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer());
5642  return {data_pointer, base_pointer};
5643  }

5645  ElementsKind kind) {

5647  GetTypedArrayDataAndBasePointers(typed_array);
5648  return __ LoadTypedElement(typed_array, base_pointer, data_pointer,
5649  __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index),
5650  GetArrayTypeFromElementsKind(kind));
5651  }

5653  V<Untagged> BuildConstantTypedArrayLoad(compiler::JSTypedArrayRef typed_array,
5654  V<Word32> index, ElementsKind kind) {

5656  // the heap.
5657  DCHECK(!typed_array.is_on_heap());

5659  __ HeapConstant(typed_array.object()), __ SmiConstant(Smi::zero()),
5660  __ WordPtrConstant(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(typed_array.data_ptr())),
5661  __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index), GetArrayTypeFromElementsKind(kind));
5662  }
