5685 
5686  V<Number> Float64ToTagged(
5687  V<Float64> input,
5688  maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode conversion_mode) {
5689  // Float64ToTagged's conversion mode is used to control whether integer
5690  // floats should be converted to Smis or to HeapNumbers: kCanonicalizeSmi
5691  // means that they can be converted to Smis, and otherwise they should
5692  // remain HeapNumbers.
5693  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind =
5694  conversion_mode ==
5695  maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi
5696  ? ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber
5697  : ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber;
5698  return V<Number>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5699  input, kind, RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5700  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kDouble,
5701  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero));
5702  }
5703 
5704  V<NumberOrUndefined> HoleyFloat64ToTagged(
5705  V<Float64> input,
5706  maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode conversion_mode) {
5707  Label<NumberOrUndefined> done(this);
5708  if (conversion_mode ==
5709  maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi) {
5710  // ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive cannot at the same time canonicalize smis
5711  // and handle holes. We thus manually insert a smi check when the
5712  // conversion_mode is CanonicalizeSmi.
5713  IF (__ Float64IsSmi(input)) {
5714  V<Word32> as_int32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(input);
5715  V<Smi> as_smi = V<Smi>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5716  as_int32, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi,
5717  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
5718  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
5719  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero));
5720  GOTO(done, as_smi);
5721  }
5722  }
5723  V<NumberOrUndefined> as_obj =
5724  V<NumberOrUndefined>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5725  input,
5726  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
5727  kHeapNumberOrUndefined,
5728  RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5729 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5730  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
5731  kDoubleOrUndefinedOrHole,
5732 #else
5733  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kDoubleOrHole,
5734 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5735  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero));
5736  if (done.has_incoming_jump()) {
5737  GOTO(done, as_obj);
5738  BIND(done, result);
5739  return result;
5740  } else {
5741  // Avoid creating a new block if {as_obj} is the only possible return
5742  // value.
5743  return as_obj;
5744  }
5745  }
5746 
5747  void FixLoopPhis(maglev::BasicBlock* loop) {
5748  DCHECK(loop->is_loop());
5749  if (!loop->has_phi()) return;
5750  for (maglev::Phi* maglev_phi : *loop->phis()) {
5751  // Note that we've already emited the backedge Goto, which means that
5752  // we're currently not in a block, which means that we need to pass
5753  // can_be_invalid=false to `Map`, otherwise it will think that we're
5754  // currently emitting unreachable operations and return
5755  // OpIndex::Invalid().
5756  constexpr bool kIndexCanBeInvalid = false;
5757  OpIndex phi_index = Map(maglev_phi, kIndexCanBeInvalid);
5758  PendingLoopPhiOp& pending_phi =
5759  __ output_graph().Get(phi_index).Cast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
5760  __ output_graph().Replace<PhiOp>(
5761  phi_index,
5762  base::VectorOf(
5763  {pending_phi.first(),
5764  Map(maglev_phi -> backedge_input(), kIndexCanBeInvalid)}),
5765  pending_phi.rep);
5766  }
5767  }
5768 
5769  RegisterRepresentation RegisterRepresentationFor(
5770  maglev::ValueRepresentation value_rep) {
5771  switch (value_rep) {
5772  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
5773  return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
5774  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
5775  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
5776  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
5777  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
5778  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
5779  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
5780  case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
5781  return RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
5782  }
5783  }
5784 
5785  // TODO(dmercadier): Using a Branch would open more optimization opportunities
5786  // for BranchElimination compared to using a Select. However, in most cases,
5787  // Maglev should avoid materializing JS booleans, so there is a good chance
5788  // that it we actually need to do it, it's because we have to, and
5789  // BranchElimination probably cannot help. Thus, using a Select rather than a
5790  // Branch leads to smaller graphs, which is generally beneficial. Still, once
5791  // the graph builder is finished, we should evaluate whether Select or Branch
5792  // is the best choice here.
5793  V<Boolean> ConvertWord32ToJSBool(V<Word32> b, bool flip = false) {
5794  V<Boolean> true_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value());
5795  V<Boolean> false_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value());
5796  if (flip) std::swap(true_idx, false_idx);
5797  return __ Select(b, true_idx, false_idx, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5798  BranchHint::kNone, SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
5799  }
5800 
5801  V<Boolean> ConvertWordPtrToJSBool(V<WordPtr> b, bool flip = false) {
5802  V<Boolean> true_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value());
5803  V<Boolean> false_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value());
5804  if (flip) std::swap(true_idx, false_idx);
5805  return __ Select(__ WordPtrEqual(b, __ WordPtrConstant(0)), false_idx,
5806  true_idx, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5807  BranchHint::kNone, SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
5808  }
5809 
5810  // This function corresponds to MaglevAssembler::ToBoolean.
5811  V<Word32> ToBit(
5812  maglev::Input input,
5813  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions assumptions) {
5814  // TODO(dmercadier): {input} in Maglev is of type Object (like, any
5815  // HeapObject or Smi). However, the implementation of ToBoolean in Maglev is
5816  // identical to the lowering of TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp(kBit) in
5817  // Turboshaft (which is done in MachineLoweringReducer), so we're using
5818  // TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp with a non-JSPrimitive input (but it
5819  // still works). We should avoid doing this to avoid any confusion. Renaming
5820  // TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged to TruncateObjectToUntagged might be the
5821  // proper fix, in particular because it seems that the Turbofan input to
5822  // this operation is indeed an Object rather than a JSPrimitive (since
5823  // we use this operation in the regular TF->TS graph builder to translate
5824  // TruncateTaggedToBit and TruncateTaggedPointerToBit).
5825  return V<Word32>::Cast(__ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged(
5826  Map(input.node()), TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit,
5827  assumptions));
5828  }
5829 
5830  // Converts a Float64 to a Word32 boolean, correctly producing 0 for NaN, by
5831  // relying on the fact that "0.0 < abs(x)" is only false for NaN and 0.
5832  V<Word32> Float64ToBit(V<Float64> input) {
5833  return __ Float64LessThan(0.0, __ Float64Abs(input));
5834  }
5835 
5836  LazyDeoptOnThrow ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(maglev::NodeBase* node) {
5837  if (!node->properties().can_throw()) return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo;
5838  const maglev::ExceptionHandlerInfo* info = node->exception_handler_info();
5839  if (info->ShouldLazyDeopt()) return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kYes;
5840  return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo;
5841  }
5842 
5843  class ThrowingScope {
5844  // In Maglev, exception handlers have no predecessors, and their Phis are a
5845  // bit special: they all correspond to interpreter registers, and get
5846  // eventually initialized with the value that their predecessors have for
5847  // the corresponding interpreter registers.
5848 
5849  // In Turboshaft, exception handlers have predecessors and contain regular
5850  // phis. Creating a ThrowingScope takes care of recording in Variables
5851  // the current value of interpreter registers (right before emitting a node
5852  // that can throw), and sets the current_catch_block of the Assembler.
5853  // Throwing operations that are emitted while the scope is active will
5854  // automatically be wired to the catch handler. Then, when calling
5855  // Process(Phi) on exception phis (= when processing the catch handler),
5856  // these Phis will be mapped to the Variable corresponding to their owning
5857  // intepreter register.
5858 
5859  public:
5860  ThrowingScope(GraphBuildingNodeProcessor* builder,
5861  maglev::NodeBase* throwing_node)
5862  : builder_(*builder) {
5863  DCHECK_EQ(__ current_catch_block(), nullptr);
5864  if (!throwing_node->properties().can_throw()) return;
5865  const maglev::ExceptionHandlerInfo* handler_info =
5866  throwing_node->exception_handler_info();
5867  if (!handler_info->HasExceptionHandler() ||
5868  handler_info->ShouldLazyDeopt()) {
5869  return;
5870  }
5871 
5872  catch_block_ = handler_info->catch_block();
5873 
5874  __ set_current_catch_block(builder_.Map(catch_block_));
5875 
5876  // We now need to prepare recording the inputs for the exception phis of
5877  // the catch handler.
5878 
5879  if (!catch_block_->has_phi()) {
5880  // Catch handler doesn't have any Phis, no need to do anything else.
5881  return;
5882  }
5883 
5884  const maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& interpreted_frame =
5885  throwing_node->lazy_deopt_info()->GetFrameForExceptionHandler(
5886  handler_info);
5887  const maglev::CompactInterpreterFrameState* compact_frame =
5888  interpreted_frame.frame_state();
5889  const maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit& maglev_unit =
5890  interpreted_frame.unit();
5891 
5892  builder_.IterCatchHandlerPhis(
5893  catch_block_, [this, compact_frame, maglev_unit](
5894  interpreter::Register owner, Variable var) {
5895  DCHECK_NE(owner, interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
5896 
5897  const maglev::ValueNode* maglev_value =
5898  compact_frame->GetValueOf(owner, maglev_unit);
5899  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(maglev_value);
5900 
5901  while (maglev_value->Is<maglev::Identity>()) {
5902  maglev_value = maglev_value->input(0).node();
5903  }
5904 
5905  if (const maglev::VirtualObject* vobj =
5906  maglev_value->TryCast<maglev::VirtualObject>()) {
5907  maglev_value = vobj->allocation();
5908  }
5909 
5910  DCHECK(!maglev_value->Is<maglev::Identity>());
5911  DCHECK(!maglev_value->Is<maglev::VirtualObject>());
5912  V<Any> ts_value = builder_.Map(maglev_value);
5913  __ SetVariable(var, ts_value);
5914  builder_.RecordRepresentation(ts_value,
5915  maglev_value->value_representation());
5916  });
5917  }
5918 
5919  ~ThrowingScope() {
5920  // Resetting the catch handler. It is always set on a case-by-case basis
5921  // before emitting a throwing node, so there is no need to "reset the
5922  // previous catch handler" or something like that, since there is no
5923  // previous handler (there is a DCHECK in the ThrowingScope constructor
5924  // checking that the current_catch_block is indeed nullptr when the scope
5925  // is created).
5926  __ set_current_catch_block(nullptr);
5927 
5928  if (catch_block_ == nullptr) return;
5929  if (!catch_block_->has_phi()) return;
5930 
5931  // We clear the Variables that we've set when initializing the scope, in
5932  // order to avoid creating Phis for such Variables. These are really only
5933  // meant to be used when translating the Phis in the catch handler, and
5934  // when the scope is destroyed, we shouldn't be in the Catch handler yet.
5935  builder_.IterCatchHandlerPhis(
5936  catch_block_, [this](interpreter::Register, Variable var) {
5937  __ SetVariable(var, V<Object>::Invalid());
5938  });
5939  }
5940 
5941  private:
5942  GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::AssemblerT& Asm() { return builder_.Asm(); }
5943  GraphBuildingNodeProcessor& builder_;
5944  const maglev::BasicBlock* catch_block_ = nullptr;
5945  };
5946 
5947  class NoThrowingScopeRequired {
5948  public:
5949  explicit NoThrowingScopeRequired(maglev::NodeBase* node) {
5950  // If this DCHECK fails, then the caller should instead use a
5951  // ThrowingScope. Additionally, all of the calls it contains should
5952  // explicitely pass LazyDeoptOnThrow.
5953  DCHECK(!node->properties().can_throw());
5954  }
5955  };
5956 
5957  template <typename Function>
5958  void IterCatchHandlerPhis(const maglev::BasicBlock* catch_block,
5959  Function&& callback) {
5960  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(catch_block);
5961  DCHECK(catch_block->has_phi());
5962  for (auto phi : *catch_block->phis()) {
5963  DCHECK(phi->is_exception_phi());
5964  interpreter::Register owner = phi->owner();
5965  if (owner == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
5966  // The accumulator exception phi corresponds to the exception object
5967  // rather than whatever value the accumulator contained before the
5968  // throwing operation. We don't need to iterate here, since there is
5969  // special handling when processing Phis to use `catch_block_begin_`
5970  // for it instead of a Variable.
5971  continue;
5972  }
5973 
5974  auto it = regs_to_vars_.find(owner.index());
5975  Variable var;
5976  if (it == regs_to_vars_.end()) {
5977  // We use a LoopInvariantVariable: if loop phis were needed, then the
5978  // Maglev value would already be a loop Phi, and we wouldn't need
5979  // Turboshaft to automatically insert a loop phi.
5980  var = __ NewLoopInvariantVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
5981  regs_to_vars_.insert({owner.index(), var});
5982  } else {
5983  var = it->second;
5984  }
5985 
5986  callback(owner, var);
5987  }
5988  }
5989 
5990  OpIndex MapPhiInput(const maglev::Input input, int input_index) {
5991  return MapPhiInput(input.node(), input_index);
5992  }
5993  OpIndex MapPhiInput(const maglev::NodeBase* node, int input_index) {
5994  if (V8_UNLIKELY(node == maglev_generator_context_node_)) {
5995  OpIndex generator_context = __ GetVariable(generator_context_);
5996  if (__ current_block()->Contains(generator_context)) {
5997  DCHECK(!__ current_block()->IsLoop());
5998  DCHECK(__ output_graph().Get(generator_context).Is<PhiOp>());
5999  // If {generator_context} is a Phi defined in the current block and it's
6000  // used as input for another Phi, then we need to use it's value from
6001  // the correct predecessor, since a Phi can't be an input to another Phi
6002  // in the same block.
6003  return __ GetPredecessorValue(generator_context_, input_index);
6004  }
6005  return generator_context;
6006  }
6007  return Map(node);
6008  }
6009 
6010  template <typename T>
6011  V<T> Map(const maglev::Input input, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
6012  return V<T>::Cast(Map(input.node(), can_be_invalid));
6013  }
6014  OpIndex Map(const maglev::Input input, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
6015  return Map(input.node(), can_be_invalid);
6016  }
6017  OpIndex Map(const maglev::NodeBase* node, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
6018  // If {can_be_invalid} is true (which it should be in most cases) and we're
6019  // currently in unreachable code, then `OpIndex::Invalid` is returned. The
6020  // only case where `can_be_invalid` is false is FixLoopPhis: this is called
6021  // after having emitted the backedge Goto, which means that we are in
6022  // unreachable code, but we know that the mappings should still exist.
6023  if (can_be_invalid && __ generating_unreachable_operations()) {
6024  return OpIndex::Invalid();
6025  }
6026  if (V8_UNLIKELY(node == maglev_generator_context_node_)) {
6027  return __ GetVariable(generator_context_);
6028  }
6029  DCHECK(node_mapping_[node].valid());
6030  return node_mapping_[node];
6031  }
6032  Block* Map(const maglev::BasicBlock* block) { return block_mapping_[block]; }
6033 
6034  void SetMap(maglev::NodeBase* node, V<Any> idx) {
6035  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
6036  DCHECK(idx.valid());
6037  DCHECK_EQ(__ output_graph().Get(idx).outputs_rep().size(), 1);
6038  node_mapping_[node] = idx;
6039  }
6040 
6041  void SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(maglev::NodeBase* node, V<Any> idx) {
6042  const Operation& op = __ output_graph().Get(idx);
6043  if (const TupleOp* tuple = op.TryCast<TupleOp>()) {
6044  // If the call returned multiple values, then in Maglev, {node} is
6045  // used as the 1st returned value, and a GetSecondReturnedValue node is
6046  // used to access the 2nd value. We thus call `SetMap` with the 1st
6047  // projection of the call, and record the 2nd projection in
6048  // {second_return_value_}, which we'll use when translating
6049  // GetSecondReturnedValue.
6050  DCHECK_EQ(tuple->input_count, 2);
6051  SetMap(node, tuple->input(0));
6052  second_return_value_ = tuple->input<Object>(1);
6053  } else {
6054  SetMap(node, idx);
6055  }
6056  }
6057 
6058  void RecordRepresentation(OpIndex idx, maglev::ValueRepresentation repr) {
6059  DCHECK_IMPLIES(maglev_representations_.contains(idx),
6060  maglev_representations_[idx] == repr);
6061  maglev_representations_[idx] = repr;
6062  }

6064  V<NativeContext> native_context() {
6065  DCHECK(native_context_.valid());
6066  return native_context_;
6067  }

6069  PipelineData* data_;
6070  Zone* temp_zone_;
6071  Isolate* isolate_ = data_->isolate();
6072  LocalIsolate* local_isolate_ = isolate_->AsLocalIsolate();
6073  JSHeapBroker* broker_ = data_->broker();
6074  LocalFactory* local_factory_ = local_isolate_->factory();
6075  AssemblerT assembler_;
6076  maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit_;
6077  ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::NodeBase*, OpIndex> node_mapping_;
6078  ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, Block*> block_mapping_;
6079  ZoneUnorderedMap<int, Variable> regs_to_vars_;
6080 
6081  V<HeapObject> undefined_value_;
6082 
6083  // The {deduplicator_} is used when building frame states containing escaped
6084  // objects. It could be a local object in `BuildFrameState`, but it's instead
6085  // defined here to recycle its memory.
6086  Deduplicator deduplicator_;
6087 
6088  // In Turboshaft, exception blocks start with a CatchBlockBegin. In Maglev,
6089  // there is no such operation, and the exception is instead populated into the
6090  // accumulator by the throwing code, and is then loaded in Maglev through an
6091  // exception phi. When emitting a Turboshaft exception block, we thus store
6092  // the CatchBlockBegin in {catch_block_begin_}, which we then use when trying
6093  // to map the exception phi corresponding to the accumulator.
6094  V<Object> catch_block_begin_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
6095 
6096  // Maglev loops can have multiple forward edges, while Turboshaft should only
6097  // have a single one. When a Maglev loop has multiple forward edges, we create
6098  // an additional Turboshaft block before (which we record in
6099  // {loop_single_edge_predecessors_}), and jumps to the loop will instead go to
6100  // this additional block, which will become the only forward predecessor of
6101  // the loop.
6102  ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, Block*>
6103  loop_single_edge_predecessors_;
6104  // When we create an additional loop predecessor for loops that have multiple
6105  // forward predecessors, we store the newly created phis in
6106  // {loop_phis_first_input_}, so that we can then use them as the first input
6107  // of the original loop phis. {loop_phis_first_input_index_} is used as an
6108  // index in {loop_phis_first_input_} in VisitPhi so that we know where to find
6109  // the first input for the current loop phi.
6110  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> loop_phis_first_input_;
6111  int loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;
6112 
6113  // Magle doesn't have projections. Instead, after nodes that return multiple
6114  // values (currently, only maglev::ForInPrepare and maglev::CallBuiltin for
6115  // some builtins), Maglev inserts a GetSecondReturnedValue node, which
6116  // basically just binds kReturnRegister1 to a ValueNode. In the
6117  // Maglev->Turboshaft translation, when we emit a builtin call with multiple
6118  // return values, we set {second_return_value_} to the 2nd projection, and
6119  // then use it when translating GetSecondReturnedValue.
6120  V<Object> second_return_value_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
6121 
6122  // {maglev_representations_} contains a map from Turboshaft OpIndex to
6123  // ValueRepresentation of the corresponding Maglev node. This is used when
6124  // translating exception phis: they might need to be re-tagged, and we need to
6125  // know the Maglev ValueRepresentation to distinguish between Float64 and
6126  // HoleyFloat64 (both of which would have Float64 RegisterRepresentation in
6127  // Turboshaft, but they need to be tagged differently).
6128  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<OpIndex, maglev::ValueRepresentation>
6129  maglev_representations_;
6130 
6131  GeneratorAnalyzer generator_analyzer_;
6132  static constexpr int kDefaultSwitchVarValue = -1;
6133  // {is_visiting_generator_main_switch_} is true if the function is a resumable
6134  // generator, and the current input block is the main dispatch switch for
6135  // resuming the generator.
6136  bool is_visiting_generator_main_switch_ = false;
6137  // {on_generator_switch_loop_} is true if the current input block is a loop
6138  // that used to be bypassed by generator resumes, and thus that needs a
6139  // secondary generator dispatch switch.
6140  bool on_generator_switch_loop_ = false;
6141  // {header_switch_input_} is the value on which secondary generator switches
6142  // should switch.
6143  Variable header_switch_input_;
6144  // When secondary dispatch switches for generators are created,
6145  // {loop_default_generator_value_} is used as the default inputs for
6146  // {header_switch_input_} for edges that weren't manually inserted in the
6147  // translation for generators.
6148  V<Word32> loop_default_generator_value_ = V<Word32>::Invalid();
6149  // If the main generator switch bypasses some loop headers, we'll need to
6150  // add an additional predecessor to these loop headers to get rid of the
6151  // bypass. If we do so, we'll need a dummy input for the loop Phis, which
6152  // we create here.
6153  V<Object> dummy_object_input_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
6154  V<Word32> dummy_word32_input_ = V<Word32>::Invalid();
6155  V<Float64> dummy_float64_input_ = V<Float64>::Invalid();
6156  // {maglev_generator_context_node_} is the 1st Maglev node that load the
6157  // context from the generator. Because of the removal of loop header bypasses,
6158  // we can end up using this node in place that's not dominated by the block
6159  // defining this node. To fix this problem, when loading the context from the
6160  // generator for the 1st time, we set {generator_context_}, and in `Map`, we
6161  // always check whether we're trying to get the generator context (=
6162  // {maglev_generator_context_node_}): if so, then we get the value from
6163  // {generator_context_} instead. Note that {generator_context_} is initialized
6164  // with a dummy value (NoContextConstant) so that valid Phis get inserted
6165  // where needed, but by construction, we'll never actually use this dummy
6166  // value.
6167  maglev::NodeBase* maglev_generator_context_node_ = nullptr;
6168  Variable generator_context_;
6169 
6170  struct GeneratorSplitEdge {
6171  Block* pre_loop_dst;
6172  Block* inside_loop_target;
6173  int switch_value;
6174  };
6175  std::unordered_map<const maglev::BasicBlock*, std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>>
6176  pre_loop_generator_blocks_;
6177 
6178  V<NativeContext> native_context_ = V<NativeContext>::Invalid();
6179  V<Object> new_target_param_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
6180  base::SmallVector<int, 16> predecessor_permutation_;
6181 
6182  std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout_;
6183 };

6185 // A wrapper around GraphBuildingNodeProcessor that takes care of
6186 // - skipping nodes when we are in Unreachable code.
6187 // - recording source positions.
6188 class NodeProcessorBase : public GraphBuildingNodeProcessor {
6189  public:
6190  using GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::GraphBuildingNodeProcessor;
6191 
6192  NodeProcessorBase(PipelineData* data, Graph& graph, Zone* temp_zone,
6193  maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit,
6194  std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout)
6195  : GraphBuildingNodeProcessor(data, graph, temp_zone,
6196  maglev_compilation_unit, bailout),
6197  graph_(graph),
6198  labeller_(maglev_compilation_unit->graph_labeller()) {}
6199 
6200  template <typename NodeT>
6201  maglev::ProcessResult Process(NodeT* node,
6202  const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
6203  if (GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Asm().generating_unreachable_operations()) {
6204  // It doesn't matter much whether we return kRemove or kContinue here,
6205  // since we'll be done with the Maglev graph anyway once this phase is
6206  // over. Maglev currently doesn't support kRemove for control nodes, so we
6207  // just return kContinue for simplicity.
6208  return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
6209  }
6210 
6211  OpIndex end_index_before = graph_.EndIndex();
6212  maglev::ProcessResult result =
6213  GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Process(node, state);
6214  DCHECK_IMPLIES(result == maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue &&
6215  !GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Asm()
6216  .generating_unreachable_operations() &&
6217  maglev::IsValueNode(node->opcode()),
6218  IsMapped(node));
6219 
6220  // Recording the SourcePositions of the OpIndex that were just created.
6221  SourcePosition source = labeller_->GetNodeProvenance(node).position;
6222  for (OpIndex idx = end_index_before; idx != graph_.EndIndex();
6223  idx = graph_.NextIndex(idx)) {
6224  graph_.source_positions()[idx] = source;
6225  }
6226 
6227  return result;
6228  }
6229 
6230  private:
6231  Graph& graph_;
6232  maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller_;
6233 };

6235 void PrintBytecode(PipelineData& data,
6236  maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info) {
6237  DCHECK(data.info()->trace_turbo_graph());
6238  maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* top_level_unit =
6239  compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit();
6240  CodeTracer* code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
6241  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(code_tracer);
6242  tracing_scope.stream()
6243  << "\n----- Bytecode before MaglevGraphBuilding -----\n"
6244  << std::endl;
6245  tracing_scope.stream() << "Function: "
6246  << Brief(*compilation_info->toplevel_function())
6247  << std::endl;
6248  BytecodeArray::Disassemble(top_level_unit->bytecode().object(),
6249  tracing_scope.stream());
6250  Print(*top_level_unit->feedback().object(), tracing_scope.stream());
6251 }

6253 void PrintMaglevGraph(PipelineData& data,
6254  maglev::Graph* maglev_graph, const char* msg) {
6255  CodeTracer* code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
6256  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(code_tracer);
6257  tracing_scope.stream() << "\n----- " << msg << " -----" << std::endl;
6258  maglev::PrintGraph(tracing_scope.stream(), maglev_graph);

6260 
6261 // TODO(dmercadier, nicohartmann): consider doing some of these optimizations on
6262 // the Turboshaft graph after the Maglev->Turboshaft translation. For instance,
6263 // MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector is the Maglev equivalent of Turbofan's
6264 // SimplifiedLowering, but is much less powerful (doesn't take truncations into
6265 // account, doesn't do proper range analysis, doesn't run a fixpoint
6266 // analysis...).
6267 void RunMaglevOptimizations(PipelineData* data,
6268  maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
6269  maglev::Graph* maglev_graph) {
6270  // Non-eager inlining.
6271  if (v8_flags.turbolev_non_eager_inlining) {
6272  maglev::MaglevInliner inliner(maglev_graph);
6273  inliner.Run(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph());
6274 
6275  maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::SweepIdentityNodes,
6276  /* visit_identity_nodes */ true>
6277  sweep;
6278  sweep.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6279  }
6280 
6281  // Phi untagging.
6282  {
6283  maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector> processor(
6284  maglev_graph);
6285  processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6286  }
6287 
6288  if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
6289  PrintMaglevGraph(*data, maglev_graph, "After phi untagging");
6290  }
6291 
6292  // Escape analysis.
6293  {
6294  maglev::GraphMultiProcessor<maglev::AnyUseMarkingProcessor> processor;
6295  processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6296  }
6297 
6298 #ifdef DEBUG
6299  maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::MaglevGraphVerifier> verifier(
6300  compilation_info);
6301  verifier.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6302 #endif
6303 
6304  // Dead nodes elimination (which, amongst other things, cleans up the left
6305  // overs of escape analysis).
6306  {
6307  maglev::GraphMultiProcessor<maglev::DeadNodeSweepingProcessor> processor;
6308  processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6309  }
6310 
6311  if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
6312  PrintMaglevGraph(*data, maglev_graph,
6313  "After escape analysis and dead node sweeping");
6314  }
6315 }
6316 
6317 std::optional<BailoutReason> TurbolevGraphBuildingPhase::Run(PipelineData* data,
6318  Zone* temp_zone,
6319  Linkage* linkage) {
6320  JSHeapBroker* broker = data->broker();
6321  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unparked_scope(broker);
6322 
6323  std::unique_ptr<maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo> compilation_info =
6324  maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo::NewForTurboshaft(
6325  data->isolate(), broker, data->info()->closure(),
6326  data->info()->osr_offset(),
6327  data->info()->function_context_specializing());
6328 
6329  // We need to be certain that the parameter count reported by our output
6330  // Code object matches what the code we compile expects. Otherwise, this
6331  // may lead to effectively signature mismatches during function calls. This
6332  // CHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure this doesn't happen.
6333  SBXCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
6334  linkage->GetIncomingDescriptor()->ParameterSlotCount());
6335 
6336  if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
6337  PrintBytecode(*data, compilation_info.get());
6338  }
6339 
6340  LocalIsolate* local_isolate = broker->local_isolate_or_isolate();
6341  maglev::Graph* maglev_graph = maglev::Graph::New(compilation_info.get());
6342 
6343  // We always create a MaglevGraphLabeller in order to record source positions.
6344  compilation_info->set_graph_labeller(new maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller());
6345 
6346  maglev::MaglevGraphBuilder maglev_graph_builder(
6347  local_isolate, compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit(),
6348  maglev_graph);
6349  maglev_graph_builder.Build();
6350 
6351  if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
6352  PrintMaglevGraph(*data, maglev_graph, "After graph building");
6353  }
6354 
6355  RunMaglevOptimizations(data, compilation_info.get(), maglev_graph);
6356 
6357  // TODO(nicohartmann): Should we have source positions here?
6358  data->InitializeGraphComponent(nullptr);
6359 
6360  std::optional<BailoutReason> bailout;
6361  maglev::GraphProcessor<NodeProcessorBase, true> builder(
6362  data, data->graph(), temp_zone,
6363  compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit(), &bailout);
6364  builder.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
6365 
6366  // Copying {inlined_functions} from Maglev to Turboshaft.
6367  for (OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder holder :
6368  maglev_graph->inlined_functions()) {
6369  data->info()->inlined_functions().push_back(holder);
6370  }
6371 
6372  if (V8_UNLIKELY(bailout.has_value() &&
6373  (v8_flags.trace_turbo || v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph))) {
6374  // If we've bailed out, then we've probably left the graph in some kind of
6375  // invalid state. We Reset it now, so that --trace-turbo doesn't try to
6376  // print an invalid graph.
6377  data->graph().Reset();
6378  }
6379 
6380  return bailout;
6381 }
6382 
6383 #include "src/compiler/turboshaft/undef-assembler-macros.inc"
6384 
6385 } // namespace v8::internal::compiler::turboshaft
